WEBVTT

00:11.678 --> 00:13.346
[explosion]

00:13.388 --> 00:25.066
[***]

00:27.318 --> 00:32.282
[***]

00:33.533 --> 00:39.622
[***]

00:42.876 --> 00:54.512
[***]

01:04.439 --> 01:05.815
[footsteps]

01:15.700 --> 01:24.626
[***]

01:29.464 --> 01:30.507
CORRESPONDENT 1 (ON TV):
As we enter the final week

01:30.548 --> 01:32.842
of this historic
three-horse race.

01:32.884 --> 01:34.719
I'm surrounded
by passionate supporters

01:34.761 --> 01:36.429
of a candidate
who burst onto the scene

01:36.471 --> 01:37.764
-no more than five months ago.
-ELI: Lucas.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.598
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Hey.

01:38.640 --> 01:39.766
Did you find him?

01:39.808 --> 01:42.185
-[indistinct chatter]
-Uh, no. Not yet.

01:42.227 --> 01:42.894
ELI (OVER CELLPHONE):
Where are you?

01:43.895 --> 01:45.271
I'm by ATB.

01:45.313 --> 01:46.606
SHARON (ON TV):
A story unheard of

01:46.648 --> 01:48.733
in the history
of American politics.

01:48.775 --> 01:50.860
One year ago,
former gold medalist,

01:50.902 --> 01:52.779
Nate Sterling,
took the political world

01:52.821 --> 01:56.783
by surprise and by storm
with his best-selling manifesto,

01:56.825 --> 01:59.828
a Declaration of Independence,
a modern-day common sense.

01:59.869 --> 02:02.872
CORRESPONDENT 2 (ON TV):
Here we are at Nate Sterling's
biggest rally yet.

02:02.914 --> 02:05.625
The independent candidate
has created a tsunami,

02:05.667 --> 02:08.461
thrashing its way through
America's two-party landscape

02:08.503 --> 02:11.506
as he leads Republican nominee
Patricia Turnbull by two points

02:11.548 --> 02:13.591
with just one week to go.

02:13.633 --> 02:15.802
The senior senator
from Tennessee beat out ten

02:15.844 --> 02:18.263
of her fellow Republicans
in the primary

02:18.304 --> 02:19.806
by courting both the moderate
and far left.

02:19.848 --> 02:21.349
CORRESPONDENT 3 (ON TV):
President Archer will need

02:22.600 --> 02:23.268
to pull off a miracle
to have any hope of securing

02:23.768 --> 02:24.436
a second term.

02:25.603 --> 02:25.645
With an approval rating
in the basement,

02:26.813 --> 02:27.272
some are calling
the Democratic incumbent

02:27.856 --> 02:28.231
a sitting duck.

02:28.940 --> 02:29.274
He's about to do a hit

02:30.316 --> 02:30.692
on Politics Nightly
with Jane Bower.

02:32.610 --> 02:33.528
JANE (ON TV):
Nate Sterling is set

02:34.612 --> 02:34.654
to take the stage
any minute now.

02:35.697 --> 02:36.364
Shit.
Call back when you get him.

02:37.907 --> 02:37.949
JANE (ON TV):
But until then,
I'm pleased to welcome

02:39.034 --> 02:39.576
Nicholas Booker,
esteemed columnist

02:41.202 --> 02:42.704
for the Washington Chronicle
and lion of the fourth state.

02:42.746 --> 02:43.830
NICK (ON TV):
Oh!

02:43.872 --> 02:45.290
You're too kind, Jane.

02:45.331 --> 02:46.499
[Jane chuckling on TV]

02:47.542 --> 02:48.376
JANE (ON TV):
The election is a dead heat.

02:49.586 --> 02:50.253
If it's anything
like the last two elections,

02:51.463 --> 02:51.921
it could come down
to a few thousand votes

02:53.465 --> 02:55.842
and a handful of swing states,
or if it's a repeat of 2000,

02:55.884 --> 02:57.844
a few hundred votes.

02:57.886 --> 03:00.597
Your column is read
by a few million.

03:00.638 --> 03:02.015
Your readers
really listen to you.

03:02.057 --> 03:03.266
They trust you.

03:03.308 --> 03:04.726
I call it like I see it.

03:04.768 --> 03:05.727
What do you see here?

03:07.020 --> 03:09.981
[crowd cheering]

03:10.023 --> 03:18.990
(***)

03:28.041 --> 03:32.003
(***)

03:33.546 --> 03:37.300
Well, I have good news
and bad news.

03:37.342 --> 03:38.551
Which do you want first?

03:38.593 --> 03:40.303
-SUPPORTER 1: Bad news!
-[Nate scoffing]

03:40.345 --> 03:42.597
NATE:
Right! Always the bad.
Here it is.

03:44.599 --> 03:48.603
My little girl
turned 21 yesterday.

03:48.645 --> 03:50.021
[crowd cheering]

03:50.063 --> 03:51.398
[sighs]

03:52.357 --> 03:54.776
And the first thing Alison did
was make sure

03:54.818 --> 03:56.361
her voter registration
was current.

03:56.403 --> 03:57.779
[crowd cheering]

03:59.489 --> 04:02.742
Ah, 21 years.

04:03.910 --> 04:05.370
Those of you with kids,
you know how fast

04:05.412 --> 04:06.913
the time goes.

04:06.955 --> 04:08.873
And as I looked at those
candles
flickering on top

04:08.915 --> 04:10.917
of that birthday cake,
it brought me back

04:10.959 --> 04:12.335
to the big moments of her life.

04:13.420 --> 04:14.713
Her first words,

04:14.754 --> 04:16.589
her first steps,
her first day of school.

04:16.631 --> 04:18.383
[crowd cheering]

04:18.425 --> 04:19.467
But then my mind wandered

04:20.635 --> 04:22.012
to all she's seen
in her young life.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.473
Terror reaching our shores.

04:26.808 --> 04:30.562
Two long and costly wars.
A great recession.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.105
A deadly global pandemic.

04:32.147 --> 04:33.940
Classrooms getting shot up
every other month.

04:33.982 --> 04:35.400
Climate getting harsher
by the day.

04:35.442 --> 04:36.693
SUPPORTERS:
Yeah!

04:36.735 --> 04:39.904
Our very capitol,
the people's house, under siege.

04:41.406 --> 04:42.615
-SUPPORTER 1: Yes!
-And the sad truth

04:43.950 --> 04:46.578
is one party fuels this rage
while the other sits

04:46.619 --> 04:47.912
on their hands
and whines about it.

04:49.330 --> 04:50.790
Now, you want the good news?

04:50.832 --> 04:51.750
SUPPORTERS:
Yeah!

04:53.418 --> 04:54.502
The good news is...

04:55.670 --> 04:57.672
my daughter Alison
turned 21 yesterday.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.799
[crowd cheering]

04:59.841 --> 05:00.759
And as she blew out

05:01.801 --> 05:02.344
those candles on top
of that cake,

05:03.094 --> 05:04.095
a funny thing happened.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.972
The flames reignited.

05:06.014 --> 05:08.475
So, she blew 'em out again.

05:08.516 --> 05:09.684
And then the flames came back
again.

05:09.726 --> 05:11.353
And no matter
how hard she tried,

05:11.394 --> 05:12.729
she couldn't blow
those candles out.

05:14.022 --> 05:15.523
And that made me think
two things.

05:16.900 --> 05:19.152
One, my wife
has a wonderful sense of humor.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.112
-And two,
-[crowd laughing]

05:21.154 --> 05:24.908
just like those candles,
we always come back.

05:24.949 --> 05:26.701
America always comes back.

05:26.743 --> 05:27.869
[crowd cheering]

05:27.911 --> 05:30.955
And we have to dig deep
and do it again.

05:30.997 --> 05:35.168
Because Alison deserves better.
Our young people deserve better.

05:35.210 --> 05:37.462
They deserve to look forward
to the future

05:37.504 --> 05:41.549
the way we used to, with hope,
with pride, with excitement.

05:41.591 --> 05:43.843
There's no more time
for cruelty or fear.

05:43.885 --> 05:47.055
There's no more time
for incompetence or inaction.

05:47.097 --> 05:51.101
Their time is up!
Our time is now!

05:51.142 --> 05:53.436
America's time is now!

05:53.478 --> 05:54.521
[crowd cheering]

05:54.562 --> 05:56.022
And if you stand with me,

05:56.064 --> 05:58.024
and you vote for me,
and you keep fighting

05:58.066 --> 05:59.734
for real change with me,

06:00.985 --> 06:04.739
I promise we will get
our fire back, too.

06:04.781 --> 06:08.743
(***)

06:13.415 --> 06:15.917
Now, let me tell you
how we're gonna do it.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.722
ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
The general election
is finally upon us.

06:28.763 --> 06:30.432
And once again, we're forced
to choose

06:30.473 --> 06:32.934
between the lesser of two evils.

06:32.976 --> 06:35.020
On one side,
a Democrat in decline,

06:35.061 --> 06:36.563
and on the other,

06:37.814 --> 06:39.441
a Republican in the pockets
of corporate America.

06:40.608 --> 06:43.069
Oh, boy, our country is mired
in a recession,

06:43.111 --> 06:45.864
the whole world's on fire,
and these are the best

06:45.905 --> 06:48.033
two people we can come up with?
I mean, come on!

06:48.074 --> 06:50.785
Good luck, everyone.
We're going to need it.

06:50.827 --> 06:52.203
GORDON:
Good news!

06:52.245 --> 06:55.081
We've been bought again.

06:55.123 --> 06:57.459
As I'm sure, some of you
have already heard,

06:57.500 --> 07:00.587
Mr. Jack Hampton
is our newest overlord.

07:00.628 --> 07:03.923
Of course, I'm gonna try
to minimize the casualties,

07:03.965 --> 07:05.508
but it's no secret,

07:05.550 --> 07:09.220
our readership
is, uh, spreading thin.

07:09.262 --> 07:12.223
If we hope to compete,
we're gonna have to get down

07:12.265 --> 07:14.476
in the mud with the pigs.

07:14.517 --> 07:17.520
And how low does Mr. Hampton
want us to go?

07:17.562 --> 07:19.606
Conspiracy clickbait?

07:19.647 --> 07:22.067
Ten thousand words
on celebrity pets?

07:22.108 --> 07:24.736
We have to evolve.

07:24.778 --> 07:26.279
The only reason
we're not worm feed

07:26.321 --> 07:29.115
like half the other papers
in this godforsaken country

07:29.157 --> 07:31.826
is because we do not stop
to tread water.

07:31.868 --> 07:35.080
If we don't keep swimmin',
we die.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.164
You.

07:36.206 --> 07:38.958
I'm looking for new,
innovative ideas.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.545
Something that will ensure
that we are all still employed

07:42.587 --> 07:44.130
come Labor Day. Hmm?

07:44.172 --> 07:46.800
We need to win the battle
for Millenials and Gen Z.

07:46.841 --> 07:49.302
-Uh-huh.
-We-- we program
around the Facebook algorithm.

07:49.344 --> 07:51.054
Expand
our social media presence.

07:51.096 --> 07:53.098
He, whose name I don't care

07:53.139 --> 07:55.767
to learn, seems to think
that because I've got grandkids

07:55.809 --> 07:58.269
born before the Internet,
I don't know

07:58.311 --> 08:00.522
that we need to expand.
Of course.

08:00.563 --> 08:03.900
I have got a whole
fucking sweatshop

08:03.942 --> 08:06.695
working like a Russian
troll farm to expand

08:06.736 --> 08:08.988
our social media presence.
Okay?

08:09.030 --> 08:11.241
I've also got an army
of halfwits

08:11.282 --> 08:12.659
twice as smart as you--

08:12.701 --> 08:14.077
A high school in West Virginia

08:14.119 --> 08:15.912
is going
to a four-day school week,

08:15.954 --> 08:17.163
because of budget cuts.

08:17.205 --> 08:18.581
I had a call
with the principal--

08:18.623 --> 08:20.583
And how's that gonna sell
papers?

08:20.625 --> 08:22.002
I thought--

08:22.043 --> 08:24.629
I mean, cutting a whole day
out of the school week--

08:24.671 --> 08:25.964
What percentage

08:26.006 --> 08:28.842
of our readership do you think
has ever set foot

08:28.883 --> 08:30.176
in West Virginia?

08:30.218 --> 08:32.971
And as for the banjo-pickers
themselves,

08:33.013 --> 08:37.017
if it ain't Fox or Infowars,
they ain't readin' it.

08:37.058 --> 08:39.102
Well, maybe that's why
they don't read the Chronicle.

08:39.144 --> 08:40.270
They got a point
calling themselves

08:40.311 --> 08:42.647
the forgotten people
and calling us

08:42.689 --> 08:44.733
condescending coastal elitists.

08:48.319 --> 08:50.864
We are elite.

08:50.905 --> 08:52.323
And if you don't start
acting like it,

08:52.365 --> 08:54.576
you're gonna be a forgotten
person before you know it.

08:54.617 --> 08:57.996
The school in question
is 90 percent minority.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.874
It's gonna make
the achievement gap even wider.

09:00.915 --> 09:02.334
Of course,
the private school kids

09:02.375 --> 09:04.085
-are gonna be just fine.
-GORDON: What else?

09:05.795 --> 09:06.796
Hmm?

09:08.256 --> 09:09.341
Nate Sterling.

09:09.382 --> 09:11.718
Ah. You again.

09:11.760 --> 09:13.928
I hear he's jumping
into the race next week.

09:13.970 --> 09:16.097
And you think
I haven't heard those rumors?

09:16.139 --> 09:18.099
It's bullshit.
It's publicity for his book.

09:18.141 --> 09:19.642
My source on the ground says

09:19.684 --> 09:22.354
he just hired Kathy Gibbs
as his campaign manager.

09:27.108 --> 09:29.903
Independents. They're like bees.

09:29.944 --> 09:32.072
Once they sting, they die.

09:32.113 --> 09:35.116
If he does announce,
he might buzz around

09:35.158 --> 09:37.702
the honey jar for a week or
two,
but nobody outside

09:37.744 --> 09:39.245
the two-party system
has ever cracked

09:39.287 --> 09:40.705
20 percent of the poles.

09:40.747 --> 09:41.873
Now, it'd be a fool's errand.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.917
His camp secretly hired

09:43.958 --> 09:47.212
a pollster to test his numbers
against potential nominees.

09:47.253 --> 09:50.006
When Turnbull secured the bid,
they saw a real opening

09:50.048 --> 09:51.132
for an independent like him.

09:52.425 --> 09:52.717
They know he's gonna have to
thread the needle,

09:53.426 --> 09:54.636
but it's not impossible.

09:54.678 --> 09:57.806
So, what are you suggesting?

10:00.141 --> 10:02.769
We get in early.

10:02.811 --> 10:04.145
Prep a cover feature.

10:04.187 --> 10:05.939
The wave is coming
with this guy.

10:05.980 --> 10:07.691
We may as well paddle out
to the break.

10:07.732 --> 10:11.111
Tell me why I would waste
my front page on this neophyte?

10:12.278 --> 10:14.823
Are you referring to me
or Sterling, sir?

10:14.864 --> 10:16.366
GORDON:
Both.

10:16.408 --> 10:19.703
You willing to bet your job
on this fever dream of yours?

10:19.744 --> 10:22.122
If we short him, we'll be
kicking ourselves later.

10:22.163 --> 10:23.957
But if we're early to the
party,
we might just sell

10:23.998 --> 10:25.291
enough papers
to give the Russian trolls

10:25.333 --> 10:27.085
an extra ten minutes
on their lunch break.

10:27.127 --> 10:30.130
[breathes deeply]

10:30.171 --> 10:31.131
Hmm.

10:32.173 --> 10:33.216
[clicks tongue]

10:33.258 --> 10:35.051
Fuck it.

10:35.093 --> 10:37.679
How can I fold
when a wounded cub is all in?

10:39.014 --> 10:42.142
Ackerman, you take the reins
on the Sterling feature.

10:42.183 --> 10:43.435
Choose your own co-pilot.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.686
I'll take Conrad.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.863
So, you're gonna give me
the source of Sterling's camp?

10:57.032 --> 10:58.700
Look, look, look, look.
I get it. I get it. All right?

10:58.742 --> 11:01.995
You wanted that story.
And that was a valiant effort.

11:02.037 --> 11:05.915
It was. But, you know,
karma is still a bitch.

11:05.957 --> 11:07.751
-And so am I.
-[chuckles]

11:07.792 --> 11:09.085
Come on. Look.

11:09.127 --> 11:10.795
It's a hard time for guys
like me right now.

11:10.837 --> 11:11.421
I mean, look around you.

11:11.463 --> 11:12.714
Oh, come on.

11:12.756 --> 11:13.465
A little awareness maybe--

11:13.506 --> 11:14.966
Okay. Thanks.

11:15.008 --> 11:17.093
Make up your mind.

11:17.135 --> 11:20.180
Either you're a victim
or a big shot.

11:20.221 --> 11:23.183
Kid gets to scoop Ackerman's
shit on his first cover story.

11:23.224 --> 11:25.810
And suddenly,
he's schizophrenic.

11:25.852 --> 11:26.895
[chuckles]
No. I was just--

11:28.188 --> 11:29.105
Were you just thanking Eli
for the opportunity?

11:31.232 --> 11:32.192
Yeah.

11:36.988 --> 11:39.240
I never liked that arrogant
little boat shoe.

11:41.242 --> 11:45.330
Email me the best thing
you've ever written.

11:53.338 --> 11:54.381
Which piece did you send him?

11:54.422 --> 11:56.383
The Honduran refugee one?

11:56.424 --> 11:58.968
-Yeah.
-Holy shit. He is gonna love it.

12:01.179 --> 12:02.430
What?

12:02.472 --> 12:03.431
Nothing.

12:08.395 --> 12:09.354
What is this?

12:12.482 --> 12:14.192
Now, when did you have time to--

12:14.234 --> 12:16.569
You've been working so hard,
I thought,

12:16.611 --> 12:19.239
"He deserves the finest grape
Safeway has on offer."

12:19.280 --> 12:20.782
Mm. [does chef's kiss]

12:20.824 --> 12:22.409
[chuckles]

12:28.790 --> 12:30.250
Penny ships off tomorrow.

12:30.291 --> 12:33.003
So, if my mom breaks down
in tears, don't be too alarmed.

12:33.044 --> 12:34.462
LUCAS:
Your mom? What about you?

12:34.504 --> 12:35.213
Remember the last time
she deployed?

12:35.255 --> 12:36.423
[Eli chuckles]

12:36.464 --> 12:37.257
ELI:
That's smart, buddy.

12:37.298 --> 12:39.259
LUCAS:
Ooh!

12:39.300 --> 12:40.468
-ELI: Hi.
-Hello.

12:40.510 --> 12:41.386
LUCAS:
Hey.

12:41.428 --> 12:44.848
To my beautiful daughters.

12:44.889 --> 12:46.433
Penelope and Elisha.

12:46.474 --> 12:49.102
One makes the news
and one reports it.

12:49.144 --> 12:50.311
[chuckles]

12:50.353 --> 12:53.356
Oh, wow.
You make it sound so romantic.

12:53.398 --> 12:55.608
Most days, I just stand
by the printer

12:55.650 --> 12:57.402
and get paper cuts.

12:57.444 --> 12:59.446
Well, you accepted the risk
when you signed up for the job.

12:59.487 --> 13:00.488
ELI:
Why don't you just go AWOL,

13:00.530 --> 13:01.990
and come bunk up with me
and Lucas?

13:02.032 --> 13:03.283
PENNY:
That'd be fun.

13:03.324 --> 13:04.451
As long as you're cool
with harboring a deserter

13:04.492 --> 13:05.952
with a warrant
out for her arrest.

13:05.994 --> 13:07.454
Let's change the subject,
shall we?

13:07.495 --> 13:10.165
-Eli has some breaking news.
-Oh.

13:10.206 --> 13:12.917
She managed to get on the radar
of one Nicholas Booker.

13:12.959 --> 13:14.919
Nicholas Booker, huh?

13:14.961 --> 13:16.421
See, now that's what you need.

13:16.463 --> 13:17.964
Your own opinion column.

13:18.006 --> 13:20.592
I'm not on the Daily Tar Heel
anymore, dad.

13:20.633 --> 13:23.136
Columns don't just drop out
of thin air at the Chronicle.

13:23.178 --> 13:25.472
Well, you wanna have a real
impact.

13:25.513 --> 13:28.308
Change minds. You need a pulpit.

13:28.350 --> 13:31.895
A column in the Chronicle
is like the pope's balcony

13:31.936 --> 13:33.563
-for Christ's sake.
-I'm working on it, daddy.

13:33.605 --> 13:36.149
I'm just saying it might take
a couple decades. That's all.

13:36.191 --> 13:40.028
The Dalai Lama was a god-king
at 2.

13:40.070 --> 13:41.279
LUCAS:
Man has a point.

13:42.489 --> 13:43.573
-Oh, yeah?
-Mm-hmm.

13:43.615 --> 13:45.367
Mm. Wow.

13:45.408 --> 13:47.243
Does the man know
that religion and politics

13:47.285 --> 13:48.620
are about the only two topics
to avoid

13:48.661 --> 13:49.913
when you got a dinner guest?

13:49.954 --> 13:51.664
HAL:
Who, Lucas?

13:51.706 --> 13:53.333
He's practically family.

13:53.375 --> 13:56.211
Speaking of, when are you two
gonna make that official?

13:56.252 --> 13:58.046
[chuckles]

13:58.088 --> 14:00.006
LUCAS:
Have you got any new additions
to your collection?

14:02.050 --> 14:02.092
-No, but wait. When are we gonna
make it official?
-No, no, no. This is important.

14:02.759 --> 14:03.510
-[laughs]
-Right.

14:09.557 --> 14:12.894
You know, I never asked you,
which one was your first?

14:14.020 --> 14:15.647
HAL:
The day we realized

14:15.689 --> 14:19.109
the government had been lying
to us all along,

14:19.150 --> 14:21.653
sending me and my friends
halfway around the world

14:21.695 --> 14:23.446
to kill and be killed.

14:23.488 --> 14:27.117
Years after, Nixon knew the war
was unwinnable.

14:27.158 --> 14:28.410
LUCAS:
Do you have a favorite?

14:28.451 --> 14:30.495
He did before it was retracted.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.372
HAL:
That's what happens
when you play fast.

14:32.414 --> 14:33.915
I wasn't playing, dad.

14:33.957 --> 14:36.459
He played me.
There's a difference.

14:36.501 --> 14:39.045
Sweetheart,
you let yourself get played.

14:39.087 --> 14:40.714
Why don't you all come in here,

14:40.755 --> 14:42.590
so we can give Penny
a proper send-off?

14:52.475 --> 14:54.436
[indistinct chatter]

14:54.477 --> 14:56.229
RECEPTIONIST:
He's in meetings all day,
but I can give you his card.

14:56.271 --> 14:57.147
ELI:
Thanks.

14:57.188 --> 14:59.566
Oh, there he goes right now.

14:59.607 --> 15:00.984
That'll be on Saturday's draw.

15:01.026 --> 15:02.152
Thank you, Sharon.

15:03.695 --> 15:05.196
ELI:
Mr. Mayfield.

15:05.238 --> 15:07.407
Eli James, Washington Chronicle.

15:07.449 --> 15:09.075
You're the one
who keeps calling.

15:09.117 --> 15:10.243
I'm doing a story

15:10.285 --> 15:11.619
on drastic cuts
in public school budgets,

15:11.661 --> 15:13.163
-and it's my understanding
that--
-I'm sorry.

15:13.204 --> 15:14.289
I'm late for a meeting.

15:20.628 --> 15:22.297
Our boys looked good this year.

15:22.339 --> 15:23.631
We play like we did
against the Tar Heels

15:25.133 --> 15:25.633
in the ACC final, we might
really have a shot next year.

15:26.301 --> 15:27.177
You're a Blue Devil?

15:27.218 --> 15:29.179
Yes, sir. Class of '08.

15:29.220 --> 15:32.223
Ah. Well, I got a few decades
on you as you can...

15:32.265 --> 15:34.059
Bowties never go out of fashion.

15:35.226 --> 15:36.644
Listen, I gotta ask,

15:36.686 --> 15:38.730
how has the recession
affected your jackpots?

15:38.772 --> 15:40.357
Oh, as it affected all of us.

15:40.398 --> 15:41.358
The numbers might have dipped
but--

15:41.399 --> 15:42.609
Well, I would have thought that

15:42.650 --> 15:44.694
jackpots would rise in the
recession.

15:44.736 --> 15:45.945
How's that?

15:45.987 --> 15:48.156
You know, a lot
more desperate daydreamers.

15:49.699 --> 15:52.660
I think you mean grown adults
and valued customers.

15:54.662 --> 15:56.790
You should go grab a ticket
yourself.

15:56.831 --> 15:58.625
Gotta be in it to win it.

15:58.667 --> 16:07.592
(***)

16:13.014 --> 16:16.643
[indistinct chatter]

16:16.685 --> 16:19.104
8:00 p.m. tonight at The Monaco.

16:19.145 --> 16:21.272
If you're not early,
you're late.

16:21.314 --> 16:23.483
[indistinct chatter]

16:37.497 --> 16:39.040
I don't have time
for pleasantries.

16:39.082 --> 16:41.084
I've got a hit on CNN
at 10:00 p.m.

16:42.168 --> 16:44.254
What are you staring at?

16:44.295 --> 16:47.090
I'm sorry. I just have read
every single one of your columns

16:47.132 --> 16:49.217
-since I was in seventh grade--
-I don't need idol worship.

16:49.259 --> 16:52.137
I need something else from you.
Sit down.

16:55.849 --> 16:58.184
I'm getting out.

16:58.226 --> 17:00.311
As soon as this election's
over, I'm turning in my quill,

17:00.353 --> 17:01.438
and moving to the country.

17:01.479 --> 17:04.274
What? No, you can't retire yet.

17:04.315 --> 17:05.567
Who are you, my accountant?

17:07.027 --> 17:07.068
Well, what good are you gonna
do
out in retirement?

17:07.902 --> 17:08.403
I'll bury myself in Bourbon.

17:09.279 --> 17:10.321
I can read fiction for a change.

17:11.489 --> 17:12.407
And I might even watch golf
on Sundays.

17:12.449 --> 17:13.742
Institutions are crumbling.

17:13.783 --> 17:15.535
Okay? Reality is under attack.

17:15.577 --> 17:18.288
You're one of the only voices
whCome on. Come on.--

17:18.329 --> 17:21.458
Tweets with cats boxing yarn
get more eyeballs

17:21.499 --> 17:23.460
than a column these days.

17:23.501 --> 17:25.086
I've had a good run.

17:25.128 --> 17:28.256
But what journalism's become,
I'm done with it.

17:29.591 --> 17:31.718
There's a reason they tell you
not to meet your heroes.

17:31.760 --> 17:33.428
Then why did you invite me here?

17:33.470 --> 17:35.263
ENRIQUE:
Mr. Booker!

17:35.305 --> 17:36.306
And how are we tonight?

17:36.348 --> 17:38.808
Ah! Can't complain, Enrique.

17:38.850 --> 17:40.685
Isn't that your job, sir?

17:40.727 --> 17:42.354
Best steak in town.

17:42.395 --> 17:43.730
Only reason I allow him
to get away

17:43.772 --> 17:44.856
with being such a smartass.

17:44.898 --> 17:46.316
[Enrique chuckles]

17:47.359 --> 17:49.110
Oh, right. Um,

17:50.320 --> 17:51.613
I...

17:54.115 --> 17:55.450
I'll just have the house salad.

17:57.369 --> 17:58.828
Bring us two rib-eye.

17:58.870 --> 18:00.163
ENRIQUE:
Rare?

18:00.205 --> 18:01.498
NICK:
Bloody.

18:01.539 --> 18:04.125
Rule number one,
you want the rib-eye,

18:04.167 --> 18:05.293
get the rib-eye.

18:06.544 --> 18:07.545
And that's the last time
I'm doing it for you.

18:09.255 --> 18:10.632
Excuse me, Enrique?

18:12.926 --> 18:14.177
Give me the house salad.

18:15.261 --> 18:17.430
And the lobster tail.

18:17.472 --> 18:18.807
And may I?

18:21.393 --> 18:25.146
A bottle of the '04 Chablis.
Feels like a good vintage.

18:26.648 --> 18:30.193
[laughs]

18:30.235 --> 18:31.277
-How are you?
-ELI: Oh.

18:31.319 --> 18:32.445
Lovely to see you.

18:32.487 --> 18:33.780
Hi, Gregg.

18:33.822 --> 18:35.907
Oh, fuck me. She's coming over.

18:39.494 --> 18:40.578
Who are you?

18:42.205 --> 18:45.166
-Eli James. Pleasure to meet
you.
-A pleasure.

18:45.208 --> 18:46.584
NICK:
Your campaign finance bill

18:46.626 --> 18:48.294
proved quite the battle,
Senator.

18:48.336 --> 18:50.422
Passed just in time
for the run-up to the generals.

18:50.463 --> 18:51.673
Flawless orchestration.

18:51.715 --> 18:53.675
Nicky never was one
for small talk.

18:53.717 --> 18:55.468
NICK:
I gave you a gold star

18:55.510 --> 18:57.595
for pulling your party
out of the insane asylum,

18:57.637 --> 18:59.514
-but this bill...
-Good bill, Nick.

18:59.556 --> 19:02.308
It's Citizens United on meth.

19:02.350 --> 19:04.477
First, corporations,
and now, individuals?

19:04.519 --> 19:06.938
Oh! She's feisty, this one.

19:06.980 --> 19:08.523
NICK:
But she's not wrong.

19:09.691 --> 19:10.900
How many of your billionaire
boy toys are bidding a path

19:11.860 --> 19:12.819
towards your bedroom
door now that you've cut

19:13.945 --> 19:14.988
the chastity belt
off their checkbooks?

19:15.030 --> 19:17.866
Before you go defaming the FSCA,

19:17.907 --> 19:20.535
you might want to look up
the word, freedom,

19:20.577 --> 19:22.203
in your pocket dictionary.

19:22.245 --> 19:22.871
Turns out, people like it.

19:22.912 --> 19:24.622
Oh, relax. Relax.

19:24.664 --> 19:27.542
I'm not gonna write about
your Free Speech Campaign Act.

19:27.584 --> 19:29.544
No? What you gonna write about?

19:29.586 --> 19:31.755
Your Fuck Small Contributions
Act.

19:31.796 --> 19:33.506
[Turnbull laughs]

19:33.548 --> 19:35.550
Listen,
I'd love to flirt all night,

19:35.592 --> 19:37.927
but my husband's a jealous man.

19:37.969 --> 19:39.846
I just came by to say,
I look forward

19:39.888 --> 19:41.473
to Sunday's column.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.850
A good shellacking
from Nicholas Booker

19:43.892 --> 19:47.687
is the best endorsement
a candidate could ask for.

19:47.729 --> 19:50.857
If you need help clarifying
the fine print on the bill,

19:50.899 --> 19:51.858
door's always open.

19:51.900 --> 19:54.319
I'll call your aide tomorrow.

19:54.361 --> 19:55.528
I wasn't talking to you.

19:56.946 --> 19:58.323
Call anytime.

19:59.741 --> 20:00.867
Don't be shy.

20:03.328 --> 20:04.537
NICK:
Rule number two,

20:04.579 --> 20:06.581
Congressmen think
they're presidents,

20:06.623 --> 20:08.875
senators think they're kings,

20:08.917 --> 20:10.919
and presidents think
they're god.

20:10.960 --> 20:13.588
Yeah, well, I'm an atheist.

20:13.630 --> 20:14.589
NICK:
Hmm.

20:15.674 --> 20:17.008
-You married?
-ELI: No.

20:17.050 --> 20:19.969
-NICK: Good. Don't.
-Is that a rule or a suggestion?

20:20.011 --> 20:22.514
I'm getting divorced again.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.474
-Fool me twice.
-ELI: Oh, I'm sorry.

20:24.516 --> 20:25.392
Oh, no, no.

20:25.433 --> 20:26.685
It's uh-- [chuckles]

20:26.726 --> 20:28.728
Congratulations
is more appropriate.

20:28.770 --> 20:29.979
Oh, well...

20:34.651 --> 20:36.027
I think you're the one.

20:37.570 --> 20:40.031
What does that mean exactly?

20:40.073 --> 20:43.743
I need someone in my corner
on these next few columns.

20:43.785 --> 20:45.495
Gonna be short on time

20:45.537 --> 20:48.540
with the old lady trying
to nail me to the cross.

20:48.581 --> 20:51.292
Plus, my TV schedule
is wall to wall

20:51.334 --> 20:53.628
with the general heating up.

20:54.838 --> 20:58.299
You be my Angelo Dundee now,

20:58.341 --> 21:01.594
and I'll be your Don King
when I get my life back.

21:01.636 --> 21:02.971
You-- you want me to--

21:03.013 --> 21:05.306
I want you to help me
with my columns.

21:07.017 --> 21:08.476
[chuckles]

21:09.519 --> 21:10.645
NICK:
I'll-- I'll tell you
what I wanna cover.

21:11.938 --> 21:14.107
You assist with research,
uh, share your notes.

21:14.149 --> 21:16.359
[clears throat]
Proof my drafts.

21:16.401 --> 21:17.944
Why me?

21:17.986 --> 21:19.612
NICK:
Don't fish. It's unseemly.

21:19.654 --> 21:20.989
No, I just--

21:21.031 --> 21:22.699
NICK:
Look. You stood up
to Gordon yesterday

21:22.741 --> 21:25.118
when most guys
who'd been there two decades

21:25.160 --> 21:27.037
sat with pricks in their hand.

21:27.078 --> 21:30.498
And your writing,
it's got punch.

21:30.540 --> 21:33.335
It's raw,
but there's something there.

21:36.671 --> 21:37.756
Wow.

21:39.507 --> 21:40.925
In the interest
of full disclosure,

21:40.967 --> 21:43.636
I was fired from the Globe.

21:43.678 --> 21:46.931
NICK:
You wanted that felon's sob
story to be true,

21:46.973 --> 21:47.974
because you had something
to say about

21:48.016 --> 21:49.893
the criminal justice system.

21:49.934 --> 21:52.979
You let ambition and bias
blind you to the fact

21:53.021 --> 21:55.648
that that fuckwit had something
to gain by bullshitting you.

21:56.983 --> 22:00.987
Moral of the story,
always follow the facts,

22:01.029 --> 22:02.781
wherever they lead.

22:02.822 --> 22:04.574
Sometimes,
it's not where you wanna go.

22:04.616 --> 22:06.409
But you go anyway.

22:07.660 --> 22:08.703
Is that rule number four?

22:08.745 --> 22:10.955
No, that's not a rule.

22:10.997 --> 22:13.041
That's a commandment.

22:13.083 --> 22:16.836
Besides, that felon
had three strikes to his name.

22:16.878 --> 22:18.171
Why shouldn't you?

22:18.213 --> 22:21.675
Mistakes
used to make you better.

22:21.716 --> 22:24.594
Now, you're not allowed
to be human.

22:24.636 --> 22:26.388
Well, fuck that!

22:26.429 --> 22:30.141
You learned your lesson,
and I'm buying the dip.

22:30.183 --> 22:31.601
What do you say?

22:34.437 --> 22:35.563
Yeah.

22:35.605 --> 22:36.690
Wonderful.

22:36.731 --> 22:37.691
Now,

22:38.942 --> 22:40.777
I'll need your notes
on Sunday's column

22:40.819 --> 22:42.404
by noon tomorrow.

22:42.445 --> 22:44.155
What's our angle?

22:44.197 --> 22:45.699
Reporters
use their eyes and ears,

22:45.740 --> 22:47.742
columnists use their brains.

22:47.784 --> 22:50.995
We'll know what my angle
is by noon tomorrow, won't we?

22:53.707 --> 22:55.625
Yeah.

22:55.667 --> 22:57.127
ANNOUNCER(ON TV):
Well, if you think Archer

22:58.753 --> 22:59.462
has a grasp on foreign policy,
then tell me why he refuses

22:59.504 --> 23:01.631
to stand up to China.

23:01.673 --> 23:04.884
I mean, we've got ten times
the military spending of Russia,

23:04.926 --> 23:07.095
and yet he cowers in the face
of the Kremlin.

23:07.137 --> 23:09.514
Look,
he's just a weak president.

23:09.556 --> 23:11.516
I'm just gonna--
I won't say it.

23:11.558 --> 23:14.602
Republicans know it,
our allies, and we all know it.

23:14.644 --> 23:15.437
And let's be honest,
the Democrats know it, too.

23:15.478 --> 23:16.980
[hums]

23:17.022 --> 23:18.606
What are you so giddy about?

23:18.648 --> 23:19.983
-Wouldn't you like to know?
-LUCAS: Oh!

23:20.025 --> 23:21.735
[Lucas chuckles]

23:21.776 --> 23:23.945
[hums]

23:23.987 --> 23:25.113
LUCAS:
How'd it go?

23:29.117 --> 23:30.076
[chuckles]

23:30.118 --> 23:33.747
[hums]

23:33.788 --> 23:35.123
-LUCAS: No.
-Oh, yeah. It's coming down.

23:35.165 --> 23:37.125
LUCAS: Get outta here.
It's coming down.

23:37.167 --> 23:38.001
LUCAS:
No.

23:38.043 --> 23:39.502
[chuckles]

23:39.544 --> 23:40.712
-Go away.
-[kisses]

23:40.754 --> 23:42.088
-ELI: I got you something.
-Oh, yeah?

23:42.130 --> 23:45.508
It's probably worth $44 million.

23:45.550 --> 23:46.593
My own private island,

23:46.634 --> 23:48.928
so I can have some peace
and quiet?

23:48.970 --> 23:52.599
Aw! Where's yours?
You didn't get one for yourself?

23:52.640 --> 23:55.935
I already won the lottery,
because I have you.

23:55.977 --> 23:58.146
How come you're never this
sweet
to me when you're sober?

23:58.188 --> 24:00.940
Koalas are sweet.

24:00.982 --> 24:02.567
I am a lion.

24:02.609 --> 24:04.277
-Oh, is that right?
-A lion.

24:04.319 --> 24:06.029
-Oh?
-A hungry lion.

24:06.071 --> 24:08.239
Oh. [chuckles]

24:08.281 --> 24:09.532
-[smooches]
-Very hungry.

24:09.574 --> 24:10.700
Oh.

24:10.742 --> 24:12.535
Very hungry.

24:14.037 --> 24:15.789
CORRESPONDENT 4 (ON TV):
Breaking news
out of the Washington Chronicle.

24:16.956 --> 24:18.500
Olympic gold medalist
and best-selling author,

24:19.834 --> 24:21.211
Nate Sterling is set to launch
an independent campaign

24:22.337 --> 24:23.588
for president next Sunday
in his hometown

24:23.630 --> 24:25.048
of Portsmouth, Ohio.

24:25.090 --> 24:27.008
The reporting
out of the Washington Chronicle

24:27.050 --> 24:29.803
claims that Sterling has hired
the highly sought-after

24:29.844 --> 24:32.681
Kathy Gibbs
as his campaign manager.

24:32.722 --> 24:35.684
While history tells us
that an independent bid faces--

24:35.725 --> 24:37.060
The Chronicle?

24:38.687 --> 24:39.896
Oh, Eli, what the fuck?

24:39.938 --> 24:41.940
Come on. Everybody knew he was
running.

24:41.981 --> 24:43.233
It was like the worst-kept
secret.

24:43.274 --> 24:45.902
Kathy Gibbs. Nobody knew about
Kathy Gibbs. Eli.

24:45.944 --> 24:47.529
ELI:
I have other sources.

24:47.570 --> 24:50.031
I wouldn't have pitched it
if I hadn't double-checked--

24:50.073 --> 24:52.075
Am I your source
or am I your boyfriend?

24:52.117 --> 24:53.993
You never said
it was off the record.

24:54.035 --> 24:55.120
You can't be serious.

24:55.161 --> 24:56.913
Sorry, Lucas. I really am.

24:56.955 --> 25:00.083
I just-- it just came out.
I-- I didn't even plan on it.

25:00.125 --> 25:03.169
And then it was out. I just...

25:03.211 --> 25:05.755
Oh, fuck, fuck, fuck.

25:05.797 --> 25:08.758
Fuck, fuck.
Who are you calling?

25:09.884 --> 25:10.927
Eli.

25:10.969 --> 25:12.303
Senator Turnbull, please.

25:12.345 --> 25:13.972
What?

25:14.014 --> 25:16.975
Eli James
from the Washington Chronicle.

25:17.017 --> 25:20.645
Senator Turnbull.
I'm sorry to call you so late.

25:20.687 --> 25:22.814
I was just wondering
if you had any thoughts

25:22.856 --> 25:25.692
on Nate Sterling
entering the race.

25:26.901 --> 25:28.028
Right now?

25:29.070 --> 25:31.781
Uh, yeah. Of course.

25:31.823 --> 25:33.033
I'll be right there.

25:33.074 --> 25:35.702
Eli. What the fuck?

25:37.245 --> 25:41.166
I just got an interview
with Patricia Turnbull.

25:41.207 --> 25:42.876
Now?

25:42.917 --> 25:44.794
Are you serious? You're drunk!

25:44.836 --> 25:47.672
Buzzed. And I wouldn't have
this interview

25:47.714 --> 25:50.050
if it wasn't for you,
so thank you so much.

25:50.091 --> 25:50.967
I love you.

25:51.009 --> 25:52.385
-[smooches]
-Wait.

25:52.427 --> 25:54.220
-Cold shower now.
-I don't have time.

25:54.262 --> 25:57.182
No, now! Give me the keys.

25:58.892 --> 26:00.643
Do not go easy on her, okay?

26:01.686 --> 26:02.771
Okay.

26:04.689 --> 26:05.815
Here.

26:07.984 --> 26:08.902
-Listen to me.
-Yes.

26:08.943 --> 26:10.153
Anything you have seen,

26:10.195 --> 26:11.780
heard, or read
under this roof...

26:11.821 --> 26:13.406
-ELI: Mm-hmm.
-Is of the fucking record...

26:13.448 --> 26:16.201
-Yeah, yeah.
-Okay?
Especially in Turnbull's office.

26:16.242 --> 26:17.827
-Yeah.
-Eli!

26:17.869 --> 26:18.953
Scout's honor.

26:18.995 --> 26:20.080
Yeah. Scout's--

26:20.121 --> 26:20.872
[smooches]

26:22.957 --> 26:25.752
Just global response.
No, we don't go for that.

26:25.794 --> 26:27.712
ELI:
Eli James for Senator Turnbull.

26:27.754 --> 26:29.339
RECEPTIONIST 2:
Please sign in.

26:29.381 --> 26:30.924
She's expecting you.

26:30.965 --> 26:32.175
TURNBULL:
Come on in, hon!

26:33.718 --> 26:34.678
Where is...

26:36.846 --> 26:37.847
ELI:
Evening, Senator.

26:37.889 --> 26:39.099
Good evening!

26:39.140 --> 26:41.768
I noticed a Tom Mayfield
on your sign-in log.

26:41.810 --> 26:44.354
Is that the same Mayfield
from SuperMillions?

26:44.396 --> 26:45.397
You know Tom?

26:45.438 --> 26:47.023
ELI:
I'm writing a story on lotto.

26:47.065 --> 26:48.066
TURNBULL:
Oh, dear.

26:49.192 --> 26:50.110
That sounds like a real
tour de force.

26:50.151 --> 26:51.820
How do you know Mr. Mayfield?

26:53.822 --> 26:55.323
TURNBULL:
You see the one in the bowtie?

26:55.365 --> 26:57.283
ELI:
Oh, my God. Is that you? Wow.

26:57.325 --> 26:58.827
He thinks because we dated

26:58.868 --> 27:00.995
30 years ago,
he can drop by unannounced

27:01.037 --> 27:03.123
with all kinds of suggestions.

27:03.164 --> 27:04.416
[laughs]

27:04.457 --> 27:05.959
I love this town.

27:06.001 --> 27:08.378
It'll even turn ex-boyfriends
into lobbyists.

27:08.420 --> 27:09.921
ELI:
Hmm.

27:13.842 --> 27:15.176
What is your reaction
to Nate Sterling

27:15.218 --> 27:16.344
entering the race?

27:17.846 --> 27:19.139
I look forward to a healthy,

27:19.180 --> 27:23.018
robust debate on the future
of our great nation.

27:23.059 --> 27:25.770
I'm not too familiar
with Mr. Sterling personally,

27:25.812 --> 27:28.314
but anyone who aspires
to serve his or her country,

27:28.356 --> 27:31.860
whether it's an Olympian,
or a lieutenant, or a president,

27:31.901 --> 27:35.030
it is okay by me.
Off the record?

27:36.239 --> 27:39.451
Mr. Sterling is swimming
with sharks,

27:39.492 --> 27:41.161
and he can't afford a cage.

27:47.208 --> 27:48.501
How would you describe

27:48.543 --> 27:51.171
your relationship
with Harvey Altman?

27:51.212 --> 27:54.174
Harvey was my senior advisor
for many years.

27:54.215 --> 27:55.467
Isn't it odd

27:55.508 --> 27:58.386
that your most trusted advisor
splits to found

27:58.428 --> 28:00.764
UpRight Super PAC
just a few weeks

28:00.805 --> 28:02.223
before you announce
your candidacy?

28:02.265 --> 28:03.183
What's odd about it?

28:03.224 --> 28:05.226
Well, UpRight is raking in

28:05.268 --> 28:07.771
loads of cash
from high-dollar donors.

28:07.812 --> 28:08.938
As is their legal right.

28:08.980 --> 28:10.190
Thanks to your bill.

28:10.231 --> 28:12.150
My bill gives Americans

28:12.192 --> 28:14.069
the freedom to do
what they please

28:14.110 --> 28:15.236
with their hard-earned money.

28:15.278 --> 28:17.197
You seem very fond of that word.
"Freedom."

28:17.238 --> 28:18.239
Oh, yes, I am.

28:19.074 --> 28:20.200
It's what this country
was built on.

28:20.241 --> 28:21.785
For some.

28:21.826 --> 28:22.827
Hmm.

28:24.329 --> 28:25.497
There are reports that Upright

28:26.915 --> 28:29.167
has raised upwards of
$80 million in just four months.

28:29.209 --> 28:30.960
-And?
-Won't that give the rich

28:31.002 --> 28:33.755
an outsized influence
in a Turnbull administration?

28:33.797 --> 28:37.008
Oh, hon. You talk about the rich
as if they're inhuman.

28:37.050 --> 28:39.010
I started my company
40 years ago

28:39.052 --> 28:42.806
with one truck
and a whole lot of elbow grease.

28:42.847 --> 28:45.475
Surely, the American dream
don't make me a bad person.

28:45.517 --> 28:48.436
I see that same fire
in your eyes right now.

28:48.478 --> 28:50.480
You didn't answer my question,
Senator.

28:52.273 --> 28:53.483
Listen, Eli.

28:56.236 --> 28:59.572
Five million from a fat wallet
and a searing column

28:59.614 --> 29:02.826
from Nicholas Booker
are one in the same.

29:02.867 --> 29:05.203
Both might get me off
on a good day.

29:05.245 --> 29:08.206
But if you think they so much
as sway my stance

29:08.248 --> 29:11.126
on the renaming of a post
office

29:11.167 --> 29:13.294
in Wasilla, Alaska,

29:13.336 --> 29:15.213
then you haven't done
your homework.

29:17.424 --> 29:19.426
Why did you invite me
here tonight?

29:19.467 --> 29:21.886
[chuckles] Oh, honey. Relax.

29:21.928 --> 29:23.972
This ain't the principal's
office.

29:24.014 --> 29:25.515
You're here,
because if there's one thing

29:25.557 --> 29:27.892
I've learned over two decades
in these chambers,

29:27.934 --> 29:30.103
it's to keep your friends close.

29:30.145 --> 29:33.273
And seeing as you'll be helping
with the most widely-read

29:33.314 --> 29:36.484
op-ed column in this country,
I figured we might get to know

29:36.526 --> 29:37.819
one another.

29:40.613 --> 29:44.075
Nick is a cheapskate.
I tip Enrique way better.

29:47.328 --> 29:49.539
[indistinct chatter]

29:49.581 --> 29:58.506
(***)

30:07.599 --> 30:16.524
(***)

30:25.617 --> 30:29.537
(***)

30:32.957 --> 30:33.667
[door knocking]

30:33.708 --> 30:35.335
Mm-hmm.

30:35.377 --> 30:37.003
Nick, can I ask you something?

30:38.546 --> 30:41.257
There's something gnawing at me
with this whole lotto.

30:41.299 --> 30:42.634
What about my column?

30:43.968 --> 30:45.387
ELI:
Wrote up my notes last night.

30:46.638 --> 30:48.014
You were drunk last night.

30:48.056 --> 30:49.140
ELI:
Just hear me out.

30:50.350 --> 30:52.435
Lotto jackpots increase
during recessions.

30:52.477 --> 30:56.272
They have for every economic
downturn as far back

30:56.314 --> 30:57.357
as the data goes.

30:57.399 --> 30:58.525
And why should I care?

30:58.566 --> 31:01.027
Because not this time.

31:01.069 --> 31:03.446
Since the recession hit,
SuperMillions' jackpots

31:03.488 --> 31:05.657
have fallen
close to five percent.

31:05.699 --> 31:07.992
-Tragic.
-It's a complete 180.

31:08.034 --> 31:10.578
A behavioral impossibility.

31:10.620 --> 31:13.039
Human nature
doesn't just reverse itself.

31:13.081 --> 31:15.458
And SuperMillions
is the only lottery

31:15.500 --> 31:16.960
that's had that kind
of inversion.

31:18.086 --> 31:19.546
Wherever you're going with
this,
get there faster.

31:19.587 --> 31:21.214
Public schools that rely

31:21.256 --> 31:23.216
on that money
are getting stiffed.

31:23.258 --> 31:25.719
So, where is the missing money
going?

31:25.760 --> 31:27.554
NICK:
This better be good.

31:27.595 --> 31:32.017
The director of SuperMillions
is a guy named Tom Mayfield.

31:32.058 --> 31:36.271
Duke alum. Class of '82.
Senator Turnbull's alma mater.

31:36.312 --> 31:37.564
They dated in college.

31:39.607 --> 31:42.027
I hope you're not suggesting
what I think you're suggesting.

31:42.068 --> 31:43.194
ELI:
The same accounting firm,

31:43.236 --> 31:45.697
Meyers & Goldstein,
handles the books

31:45.739 --> 31:48.700
for both SuperMillions
and UpRight.

31:50.452 --> 31:53.496
You think that
Mayfield and Turnbull

31:53.538 --> 31:55.582
are embezzling funds
from the lottery,

31:55.623 --> 31:58.710
and smuggling
into her largest Super PAC?

31:58.752 --> 32:00.628
At the expense of our nation's
public schools.

32:02.005 --> 32:04.215
[laughs]

32:04.257 --> 32:07.052
Everything's a fucking
conspiracy.

32:07.093 --> 32:09.387
UpRight's books are sealed shut.

32:09.429 --> 32:11.222
Thanks to Turnbull's bill,
they don't have to report

32:11.264 --> 32:12.390
where the money comes from.

32:13.641 --> 32:13.975
It could all be happening
under the same roof,

32:15.185 --> 32:15.977
-behind closed doors.
-Don't be that guy.

32:17.145 --> 32:18.646
-What guy?
-The bug-eyed virtual vigilante,

32:18.688 --> 32:22.108
running a bullshit blog
and a libelous YouTube channel

32:22.150 --> 32:23.610
out of her parents' basement.

32:23.651 --> 32:26.780
Okay. Tom Mayfield was
in Turnbull's office last night.

32:26.821 --> 32:28.406
I saw his name on the log-in.

32:28.448 --> 32:29.741
-Maybe they're still fucking.
-ELI: Nick.

32:29.783 --> 32:30.992
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

32:31.910 --> 32:33.703
-Um, reigniting the spark.
-I'm serious.

32:33.745 --> 32:36.581
Turnbull's a bully
and a misguided idea log.

32:36.623 --> 32:37.540
She's not a crook.

32:39.542 --> 32:42.671
All I'm asking you to do
is to, you know,

32:42.712 --> 32:44.631
go into that legendary rolodex
of yours,

32:44.673 --> 32:46.508
and make one or two calls.

32:46.549 --> 32:48.468
See if there's a relationship
between the top brass

32:48.510 --> 32:51.471
at Meyers & Goldstein
and anyone in Turnbull's camp.

32:51.513 --> 32:55.016
If there's nothing there,
I will drop it. I promise.

32:58.269 --> 33:00.397
GIBBS:
How the fuck did this leak?

33:00.438 --> 33:01.189
NATE:
All right. It's done.

33:01.231 --> 33:02.357
Let's move forward.

33:02.399 --> 33:03.650
This might actually help us?

33:03.692 --> 33:05.026
GIBBS:
How's that?

33:05.068 --> 33:09.656
A full week for the word
to spread means more people.

33:09.698 --> 33:11.825
A ton more people.

33:11.866 --> 33:13.576
Bigger crowd means
more media attention,

33:13.618 --> 33:15.704
which might bring us
an air of legitimacy

33:15.745 --> 33:16.705
from the jump.

33:19.416 --> 33:22.168
I drafted a statement
last night.

33:22.210 --> 33:24.254
Get it out ASAP and get to work

33:24.295 --> 33:28.216
on as many appearances
as you possibly can.

33:28.258 --> 33:31.720
Uh, local morning shows,
county fairs. You name it.

33:31.761 --> 33:35.181
We play this right,
soon, it'll be Late Night.

33:35.223 --> 33:39.269
And if we're lucky,
SNL will come calling.

33:39.310 --> 33:40.812
Got it?

33:40.854 --> 33:42.439
Good. Let's get to work.

33:42.480 --> 33:44.566
Oh. And, Lucas, pack your bags.

33:44.607 --> 33:46.693
What?

33:46.735 --> 33:47.902
You're gonna be living

33:47.944 --> 33:49.738
on the campaign bus
for the next few months.

33:49.779 --> 33:52.157
I hope you like
cornfields and Big Macs.

33:54.117 --> 33:55.785
Who doesn't?

33:55.827 --> 33:56.745
NATE:
Lucas.

34:01.291 --> 34:02.542
You know that I know, right?

34:02.584 --> 34:03.668
Nate, I am so sorry.

34:03.710 --> 34:05.211
NATE:
That's all right.

34:05.253 --> 34:06.212
Wouldn't be here without you.

34:07.630 --> 34:08.798
And if I can't roll
with the punches,

34:08.840 --> 34:10.133
I shouldn't be running
for president.

34:11.301 --> 34:14.304
But we're building
something here.

34:14.346 --> 34:15.472
Something bigger than ourselves.

34:17.140 --> 34:19.476
So, from here on out,
let's just keep things

34:19.517 --> 34:21.353
close to the chest, okay?

34:21.394 --> 34:22.437
Even in your own house.

34:25.607 --> 34:28.443
Pretend you're in the CIA.
See you on the campaign bus.

34:32.155 --> 34:34.240
[exhales deeply]

34:34.282 --> 34:36.576
[indistinct chatter]

34:47.671 --> 34:49.381
You double-checked
the lotto stats?

34:49.422 --> 34:50.799
Triple-checked.

34:50.840 --> 34:51.800
Let's go.

34:55.261 --> 34:59.516
The CEO of Meyers & Goldstein
hosted two private fundraisers

34:59.557 --> 35:01.601
for Turnbull
at his country house

35:01.643 --> 35:02.644
during the primaries.

35:02.686 --> 35:04.437
It's probably
just a coincidence.

35:04.479 --> 35:07.774
But fishy enough for us
to follow the scent.

35:07.816 --> 35:10.610
Well, there's still something
I can't wrap my head around.

35:10.652 --> 35:12.570
If they really are cooking
the books,

35:12.612 --> 35:14.531
why are they willing to risk
years behind bars?

35:14.572 --> 35:16.950
Government shells out
500 billion a year

35:16.991 --> 35:18.952
in contracts
to the private sector.

35:18.993 --> 35:20.620
Meyers & Goldstein's
bread and butter.

35:20.662 --> 35:22.789
Right. So, what now?

35:22.831 --> 35:24.207
NICK:
Well, we get someone

35:24.249 --> 35:27.961
on the inside to help us
find proof and blow the whistle.

35:28.003 --> 35:29.921
ELI:
How do we do that?

35:29.963 --> 35:31.589
NICK:
That's a good question.

35:33.341 --> 35:35.301
I've got a neighbor
who pushes paper

35:35.343 --> 35:36.594
for Meyers & Goldstein.

35:37.846 --> 35:39.723
Got his kid into kindergarten.

35:39.764 --> 35:40.473
[chuckles]

35:41.016 --> 35:43.601
Fuck, I love this town.

35:44.978 --> 35:48.940
I help this poor guy piss away
30K in glorified daycare,

35:48.982 --> 35:50.900
and he owes me a favor.

35:50.942 --> 35:52.318
So, you'll get him
to fish around?

35:52.360 --> 35:53.653
No, no, no, no.

35:53.695 --> 35:54.696
He wouldn't do that.

35:56.364 --> 35:58.616
He thinks that Turnbull
is Reagan in pearls.

35:58.658 --> 35:59.576
[chuckles softly]

35:59.617 --> 36:01.327
No.

36:01.369 --> 36:04.581
But I have got you an interview
with his associate in PR.

36:04.622 --> 36:08.585
So, go! Go.
Recruit us a double agent.

36:08.626 --> 36:10.337
Ooh. Where are you going?

36:10.378 --> 36:12.505
I've got my own interview.

36:12.547 --> 36:13.673
ELI:
With who?

36:13.715 --> 36:16.301
At worst,
your generation's Ralph Nader.

36:16.343 --> 36:18.511
At best,
the second coming of Christ.

36:18.553 --> 36:22.390
Although something tells me,
he's somewhere in between.

36:22.432 --> 36:31.399
(***)

36:40.450 --> 36:49.417
(***)

36:52.671 --> 36:54.297
JENNIFER:
We're a perennial benefactor

36:54.339 --> 36:56.716
of the Boys and Girls Club
of DC, and this year,

36:56.758 --> 36:58.635
we've implemented
a company-wide day of service

36:58.677 --> 37:00.053
with Habitat for Humanity.

37:00.095 --> 37:01.596
Wow.

37:01.638 --> 37:04.724
It must be so rewarding,
giving inner-city kids

37:04.766 --> 37:05.725
safe places to grow.

37:05.767 --> 37:07.268
Hmm. It really is.

37:07.310 --> 37:07.977
[chuckles]

37:08.019 --> 37:08.937
Is that your little one?

37:10.063 --> 37:11.606
JENNIFER:
Mm!
[chuckles]

37:11.648 --> 37:12.732
That's my Maya.

37:12.774 --> 37:14.984
ELI:
She is really beautiful.

37:15.026 --> 37:16.027
Isn't she? [laughs]

37:16.069 --> 37:17.737
Look at those cheeks!

37:17.779 --> 37:19.447
You're so sweet.
Do you have kids?

37:19.489 --> 37:20.490
Maybe one day.

37:20.532 --> 37:22.951
But for now, this is my baby.

37:24.369 --> 37:25.704
So, Ms. Cooke--

37:25.745 --> 37:27.497
Oh, please call me, "Jennifer".

37:28.623 --> 37:30.291
Jennifer.

37:30.333 --> 37:32.752
How do your company's
charitable donations compare

37:32.794 --> 37:34.629
to its political donations?

37:36.506 --> 37:38.383
I knew you'd throw
a hard ball sooner or later.

37:38.425 --> 37:39.467
[chuckles]

37:39.509 --> 37:41.761
But I'm not privy
to that information.

37:41.803 --> 37:43.638
If you'd like to chat
about our sustainability--

37:43.680 --> 37:46.891
What is your opinion
on Senator Patricia Turnbull?

37:46.933 --> 37:48.435
You mean personally?

37:48.476 --> 37:50.311
I, uh... [chuckles nervously]

37:50.353 --> 37:51.604
-What does this have to do--
-Some people think

37:51.646 --> 37:53.314
she would set the country
back 50 years.

37:55.316 --> 37:56.860
Listen. Between you and me,
I think she'd set

37:56.901 --> 37:58.903
the country back 100 years.

37:58.945 --> 38:01.364
But I don't understand
why you wanna talk to me--

38:01.406 --> 38:02.449
ELI:
Meyers & Goldstein

38:02.490 --> 38:04.576
handles the books
for SuperMillions

38:04.617 --> 38:08.580
and for Turnbull's Super PAC,
UpRight.

38:08.621 --> 38:09.622
Isn't that correct?

38:10.832 --> 38:12.917
I'm sorry. I can't discuss--

38:12.959 --> 38:15.128
Who handles those accounts?

38:15.170 --> 38:17.464
-I'm not authorized--
-Does the same executive
cover both?

38:17.505 --> 38:18.840
Okay. I think
I'm gonna have to ask you

38:18.882 --> 38:20.383
-to leave--
-Please. Jennifer.

38:20.425 --> 38:21.593
If you don't tell me
what this is about--

38:21.634 --> 38:23.136
I, too, think Patricia Turnbull

38:23.178 --> 38:26.473
is on the wrong side of
history,
and potentially, the law.

38:27.974 --> 38:29.684
I think
you're gonna wanna see this.

38:33.688 --> 38:37.442
[pants]

38:37.484 --> 38:38.985
Planning for a comeback?

38:39.027 --> 38:41.029
NATE:
Running for president

38:41.071 --> 38:43.448
is more grueling
than decathlon.

38:43.490 --> 38:45.450
[grunts]

38:45.492 --> 38:48.912
I'm surprised
you didn't cancel our interview.

38:48.953 --> 38:50.830
Why? 'Cause your team
did a better job than mine?

38:50.872 --> 38:52.082
Hmm.

38:53.625 --> 38:55.460
My day maybe a bit more hectic
thanks to the Chronicle,

38:55.502 --> 38:57.420
but I always keep
my commitments.

38:57.462 --> 38:58.380
NICK:
All right.

38:59.464 --> 39:00.548
First question.

39:02.384 --> 39:03.551
Why?

39:03.593 --> 39:04.844
Why? [chuckles]

39:04.886 --> 39:06.012
NICK:
Yeah. I mean, you could earn
millions,

39:06.054 --> 39:07.931
slapping your face
on that protein shake,

39:07.972 --> 39:09.849
and spending your time
golfing and fishing.

39:09.891 --> 39:11.184
You know, not a bad life.

39:11.226 --> 39:13.520
So, again, I ask you, why?

39:15.146 --> 39:16.106
Because I suck at golf.

39:16.147 --> 39:18.024
[chuckles]

39:18.066 --> 39:19.067
NICK:
We've seen what happens

39:19.859 --> 39:21.069
when a narcissist
with no experience

39:22.028 --> 39:23.655
turns delusions of grandeur
into reality.

39:23.697 --> 39:26.533
So, you tell me
why this isn't anything

39:26.574 --> 39:27.784
more than a vanity run?

39:27.826 --> 39:29.536
Look, I think it's only fair

39:29.577 --> 39:30.829
you give me an honest
evaluation
before you diagnose me,

39:30.870 --> 39:32.414
Mr. Booker.

39:32.455 --> 39:33.665
I'm not just coming
from the locker room

39:33.707 --> 39:35.041
to the debate stage.

39:35.083 --> 39:35.917
I went to Yale.

39:36.626 --> 39:37.419
NICK:
Oh, yeah. Law school.

39:38.586 --> 39:38.795
And your foundation's done
a lot of good,

39:39.879 --> 39:40.964
but you're up against
two candidates

39:41.006 --> 39:42.882
with damn near
a century's experience

39:42.924 --> 39:43.925
between them.

39:44.718 --> 39:45.844
How's that worked out for us,
huh?

39:46.761 --> 39:48.430
You checked your
retirement portfolio lately?

39:48.471 --> 39:49.681
Have you been
to any of these towns

39:49.723 --> 39:51.891
destroyed by flash floods
or forest fires?

39:51.933 --> 39:54.728
You checked the numbers
on drug overdoses or suicides?

39:54.769 --> 39:56.980
Shit! Life expectancy's gone
down for the first time

39:57.022 --> 39:57.939
in decades.

40:00.150 --> 40:02.610
People are desperate out there.

40:02.652 --> 40:03.945
They want somebody
to do something about it.

40:03.987 --> 40:05.697
Somebody to invest
in our future,

40:05.739 --> 40:08.116
not for the next four years,
but for the next 40 years.

40:12.871 --> 40:14.664
What, do I have something
in my teeth?

40:14.706 --> 40:16.249
NICK:
No.

40:16.291 --> 40:18.626
I'm just trying to figure out if
you're for real or full of shit.

40:18.668 --> 40:19.586
That is for you to decide.

40:20.754 --> 40:22.255
I assure you,
my work was very real

40:22.297 --> 40:24.466
to tens of thousands
of grieving families.

40:24.507 --> 40:26.676
Well, you surely made
some very powerful enemies.

40:26.718 --> 40:28.470
NATE:
Who? Big drug companies?

40:28.511 --> 40:29.971
They were selling
bold-faced lies.

40:30.013 --> 40:32.932
Claiming oxy wasn't addictive.
Let me ask you a question.

40:32.974 --> 40:34.976
How much do you think the NRA
spend on lobbying every year?

40:35.018 --> 40:36.102
Two, three million?

40:36.144 --> 40:37.312
NATE:
Correct.

40:37.354 --> 40:38.813
What do you think big pharma
spent last year?

40:40.523 --> 40:42.233
300 million.

40:42.275 --> 40:44.611
-They say they got nothing
to hide?
-[Nick chuckles]

40:44.652 --> 40:47.530
And that's why my heart
medicine
costs more than my alimony.

40:47.572 --> 40:49.199
-[Nate chuckles]
-We're gonna do something
about that, too.

40:49.240 --> 40:50.241
Oh, my ex-wife?

40:50.283 --> 40:51.159
Please, please do.

40:51.201 --> 40:52.827
[chuckles]

40:56.915 --> 40:59.125
Look me in the eye.

40:59.167 --> 41:00.919
And tell me why you think
you can win.

41:02.837 --> 41:04.631
'Cause I'll tell you
what Vegas thinks.

41:05.799 --> 41:07.801
You don't stand a chance.
Then what?

41:07.842 --> 41:10.053
You peel off enough votes
from the president

41:10.095 --> 41:13.515
to hand Turnbull the election
on a silver platter.

41:14.933 --> 41:15.934
I don't play for silver.

41:20.188 --> 41:21.731
ELI:
If you are able

41:21.773 --> 41:23.817
to get me any information
at all,

41:23.858 --> 41:26.111
emails, financials,
expense reports, don't--

41:26.152 --> 41:28.571
Okay, listen. I'm gonna stop you
right there.

41:28.613 --> 41:29.739
There has to be another way
for you

41:29.781 --> 41:30.699
to get
the information you need.

41:30.740 --> 41:31.991
And what if I can't?

41:32.033 --> 41:33.284
Then what?

41:33.326 --> 41:35.245
Do we just let them get away
with it?

41:35.286 --> 41:36.996
Your bosses could be committing
a crime

41:37.038 --> 41:38.998
that has devastating
ripple effects,

41:39.040 --> 41:42.085
and it would be a crime
with no consequence,

41:42.127 --> 41:44.045
no punishment,
no accountability.

41:45.630 --> 41:47.340
But that's just the way
the world works I guess. Right?

41:47.382 --> 41:48.925
Nothing we can do about it.

41:48.967 --> 41:51.177
Pardon me, but fuck that.

41:51.219 --> 41:52.721
This time, we can.

41:54.222 --> 41:56.599
I'm sorry.

41:56.641 --> 41:57.851
I have my daughter
to think about.

42:02.647 --> 42:03.606
Of course.

42:15.744 --> 42:18.997
I hear there's a real bad cold
going around.

42:19.039 --> 42:21.082
If you have to cough, it's
okay.
I'll understand.

42:24.169 --> 42:27.839
Robert Friedman,
Rebecca Carter...

42:29.716 --> 42:32.677
Ben Florence, Amy Parker...

42:34.262 --> 42:35.221
Spencer Erickson.

42:35.263 --> 42:36.181
[Jennifer coughs]

42:39.017 --> 42:39.934
You need to leave.

42:41.770 --> 42:44.022
Please. Don't contact me again.

42:47.067 --> 42:48.068
Thank you.

42:48.109 --> 42:52.030
(***)

42:56.284 --> 42:57.285
[sighs]

42:59.412 --> 43:01.289
[indistinct chatter]

43:12.050 --> 43:13.343
SPENCER:
I spoke with Tom this morning.

43:14.427 --> 43:16.096
That's right.

43:16.137 --> 43:18.264
Okay, I'll talk to Dean,
and have him CC you

43:18.306 --> 43:20.809
on the latest approval,
so we're all on the same page.

43:20.850 --> 43:29.818
(***)

43:38.868 --> 43:47.836
(***)

43:56.094 --> 43:57.053
[indistinct chatter]

44:01.099 --> 44:02.267
NICK:
You're kidding me.

44:03.685 --> 44:04.394
Yeah. Gordon didn't have
the decency to do it himself.

44:06.271 --> 44:07.856
Son of a bitch.

44:07.897 --> 44:11.860
(***)

44:12.944 --> 44:14.320
You cut our three best

44:14.362 --> 44:16.156
investigative reporters
and leave

44:16.197 --> 44:18.408
the whole damn sports page
intact?

44:18.450 --> 44:19.701
Relax, Nick.

44:20.660 --> 44:21.995
Nothing I can do.
This came down from above.

44:22.037 --> 44:23.872
Oh, yeah.
Like the Ten Commandments.

44:23.913 --> 44:25.707
And you sure as fuck
didn't follow any of those.

44:25.749 --> 44:27.167
Look, we're bleeding cash.

44:27.208 --> 44:29.002
And the investigative team
is among

44:29.044 --> 44:30.712
the highest-salaried employees.

44:30.754 --> 44:33.006
First, they came
for the journalists.

44:33.048 --> 44:34.466
We don't know what happened
after that.

44:34.507 --> 44:36.009
Don't be so goddamn dramatic.

44:36.051 --> 44:38.470
Well, you're the one
who dropped the fucking curtain!

44:38.511 --> 44:41.014
Soon, we'll be no better
than the National Enquirer.

44:41.056 --> 44:42.432
I told you,

44:42.474 --> 44:43.516
we're gonna have to get down
in the mud with the pigs.

44:43.558 --> 44:45.143
Times have changed.

44:45.185 --> 44:46.227
NICK:
Oh, yeah?

44:46.269 --> 44:47.771
What do you suggest
we do about it?

44:47.812 --> 44:49.064
I suggest you keep
your head down,

44:49.105 --> 44:50.523
and let me worry about it.

44:50.565 --> 44:52.067
This is so weak, Gordon.

44:53.860 --> 44:55.028
I always knew you were a prick,

44:55.070 --> 44:56.863
but I never thought
you were a pushover.

44:56.905 --> 44:59.449
We need to hold
our best reporters tight.

45:00.909 --> 45:02.911
If there's no one to defend
the truth,

45:02.952 --> 45:05.205
then we live
in a fact-free world.

45:05.246 --> 45:07.082
And that's a scary fucking
place
to live.

45:08.249 --> 45:10.085
What's your column
about this week?

45:13.338 --> 45:15.048
You've never asked that before.

45:15.090 --> 45:17.884
Mr. Hampton would strongly

45:17.926 --> 45:20.095
prefer you stay out
of the New York senate race.

45:20.136 --> 45:21.388
Oh, well, then you can tell

45:21.429 --> 45:24.015
Mr. Hampton
that I strongly prefer

45:24.057 --> 45:25.475
he go fuck himself.

45:27.310 --> 45:28.269
Yeah.

45:37.946 --> 45:46.913
(***)

45:55.964 --> 46:04.931
(***)

46:13.982 --> 46:22.949
(***)

46:32.000 --> 46:40.967
(***)

46:43.595 --> 46:45.221
-MAN: Yeah, I got it.
-SPENCER: All right?

46:45.263 --> 46:46.973
I wish you'd gotten
that promotion.

46:47.015 --> 46:48.475
Please get it done, okay?
Thank you.

46:48.516 --> 46:52.479
(***)

46:55.648 --> 46:56.900
[Spencer grunts softly]

46:56.941 --> 47:00.862
(***)

47:08.495 --> 47:10.538
-Hey, hon.
-[woman speaking indistinctly]

47:10.580 --> 47:12.624
SPENCER:
I'm at the office late tonight.

47:12.665 --> 47:14.626
[woman speaking indistinctly]

47:14.668 --> 47:17.170
Okay. Okay. I'll pick him up.

47:17.212 --> 47:19.964
But I'm gonna drop him home
and head right back in.

47:20.006 --> 47:23.093
-[woman speaking indistinctly]
-SPENCER: Yeah, it's killing me.

47:23.134 --> 47:24.511
-WOMAN 1 (OVER CELLPHONE): Love
you.
-SPENCER: Love you, too.

47:24.552 --> 47:33.520
(***)

47:37.399 --> 47:39.025
CORRESPONDENT 5 (ON TV):
Senator Patricia Turnbull

47:39.067 --> 47:41.361
has altered
her campaign schedule,

47:41.403 --> 47:43.905
adding a stop in Ohio
next Sunday in what appears...

47:43.947 --> 47:44.906
Yeah.

47:48.410 --> 47:49.411
ELI:
There's your haystack.

47:51.538 --> 47:52.914
Holy shit!

47:54.416 --> 47:55.333
Who's your source?

47:56.668 --> 47:58.420
That's confidential.

47:58.461 --> 48:00.255
Is it the PR associate?

48:01.965 --> 48:03.174
I got you the damn interview.

48:04.259 --> 48:06.177
What's your angle?

48:06.219 --> 48:07.012
You want top byline?

48:07.053 --> 48:08.930
No. I just-- I don't think--

48:08.972 --> 48:11.433
Who is the goddamn
whistleblower?

48:16.271 --> 48:17.230
You stole it?

48:17.272 --> 48:18.189
It's everything we need.

48:24.029 --> 48:26.698
They don't give Pulitzers
to fucking shoplifters.

48:26.740 --> 48:28.491
I hit a dead-end.

48:28.533 --> 48:30.243
And so, I made a judgment call.

48:30.285 --> 48:32.245
Something this big,
the ends justify the means.

48:32.287 --> 48:35.123
The ends? For who?

48:35.165 --> 48:37.959
-For you!
-No! The American people!

48:38.001 --> 48:39.419
NICK:
Bullshit!

48:39.461 --> 48:41.087
I should have you fired.

48:41.129 --> 48:42.589
ELI:
You're the one
who should be fired.

48:42.630 --> 48:44.174
You are phoning it in
right in the middle

48:44.215 --> 48:45.342
of one of the most crucial
elections

48:45.383 --> 48:47.052
of both of our lifetimes.

48:47.093 --> 48:48.261
Where is the integrity in that?

48:48.303 --> 48:50.096
Have fun
back at the kids' table,

48:50.138 --> 48:52.724
scooping up
Kevin Conrad's scraps!

48:52.766 --> 48:55.769
Please! Somewhere in that pile
is the story of a lifetime.

48:55.810 --> 48:57.729
I have no desire to commit

48:57.771 --> 49:00.440
career suicide just before
the Lifetime Achievements

49:00.482 --> 49:02.400
start rolling in
on the back of my pension.

49:03.568 --> 49:05.987
Literal suicide
is a different question.

49:06.029 --> 49:09.449
But you're not my therapist.
Now, get out of my office!

49:09.491 --> 49:10.784
We're done!

49:10.825 --> 49:13.578
-[indistinct chatter]
-[breathes shakily]

49:13.620 --> 49:22.545
(***)

49:31.638 --> 49:40.563
(***)

49:42.691 --> 49:43.775
CORRESPONDENT 6 (ON TV):
Senator Turnbull leads

49:44.818 --> 49:46.194
all candidates
in total campaign spend,

49:47.696 --> 49:48.822
having raised more cash
than both Sterling and Archer

49:48.863 --> 49:50.073
for the third month in a row.

49:51.157 --> 49:51.199
CORRESPONDENT 7 (ON TV):
In a surprise to many,

49:52.617 --> 49:54.119
Nate Sterling has gained steam
heading into July.

49:55.453 --> 49:57.414
He now sits just six points
back from President Archer

49:57.455 --> 49:59.332
and eight points back from...

50:00.875 --> 50:01.418
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Eli, something special
is happening here.

50:02.627 --> 50:02.669
The stump speeches
are starting to feel

50:03.378 --> 50:04.671
like rock concerts.

50:04.713 --> 50:06.381
I wish you were here to see it.

50:08.508 --> 50:11.344
CORRESPONDENT 8 (ON TV):
Some school districts are moving
to a four-day school week.

50:11.386 --> 50:12.846
School boards
and superintendents

50:12.887 --> 50:15.348
across the nation blame
the recession,

50:15.390 --> 50:18.601
which has caused local tax
revenues to fall off the cliff.

50:18.643 --> 50:21.396
Teachers have have taken
to GoFundMe campaigns

50:21.438 --> 50:24.399
just to acquire the bare minimum
of school supplies.

50:26.609 --> 50:28.820
WOMAN 2:
So the truth is I just
didn't think it was worth it.

50:28.862 --> 50:30.155
-SPENCER: Yeah.
-WOMAN 2: Yeah.

50:30.196 --> 50:32.073
[indistinct speech]

50:32.115 --> 50:34.617
-Take it easy.
-WOMAN 1: Take care.

50:34.659 --> 50:36.578
I'm headed to dinner
with Harvey Altman.

50:37.704 --> 50:38.621
How do I look?

50:40.331 --> 50:41.374
Like a man in a tie.

50:41.416 --> 50:42.792
[chuckles]

50:44.377 --> 50:45.712
It wouldn't hurt to give a guy
a compliment once in a while.

50:45.754 --> 50:47.505
Uh, about this email

50:47.547 --> 50:49.591
encouraging us to donate
to UpRight Super PAC...

50:49.632 --> 50:51.718
Yeah.
I already gave 'em five grand.

50:51.760 --> 50:53.803
I don't exactly feel
comfortable.

50:53.845 --> 50:55.680
Don't be cheap.
Just throw 'em a few bucks.

50:55.722 --> 50:57.432
Keep the boss happy.

50:57.474 --> 50:58.433
And if I don't?

50:59.893 --> 51:02.395
You never talked back
when you were my assistant.

51:02.437 --> 51:03.521
I kinda like it.

51:05.482 --> 51:08.485
[breathes deeply]

51:13.490 --> 51:22.457
(***)

51:31.508 --> 51:35.470
(***)

51:40.809 --> 51:43.228
[indistinct chatter]

51:43.269 --> 51:52.237
(***)

52:01.287 --> 52:10.255
(***)

52:19.305 --> 52:28.273
(***)

52:37.323 --> 52:46.291
(***)

52:50.295 --> 52:51.671
Oh, God.

52:51.713 --> 52:56.343
(***)

52:56.384 --> 52:57.344
Hello?

52:57.385 --> 53:01.348
(***)

53:02.891 --> 53:03.892
How long have you known?

53:05.935 --> 53:07.479
Six months.

53:07.520 --> 53:09.356
Why didn't you tell me?

53:09.397 --> 53:11.524
You had enough to worry about.

53:11.566 --> 53:14.819
And Penny
was going back overseas.

53:14.861 --> 53:16.321
How bad is it?

53:16.363 --> 53:17.781
That's why I called.

53:18.990 --> 53:21.576
I met with the oncologist
this morning, and...

53:23.870 --> 53:24.829
well...

53:29.751 --> 53:31.586
HAL:
Go ahead, Eli.

53:32.629 --> 53:33.630
You can say it.

53:34.464 --> 53:35.840
I mean,
I should've quit years ago.

53:39.260 --> 53:41.888
We'll find the best doctors.
We-- we--

53:41.930 --> 53:43.723
I'm on top of it.
[chuckles]

53:43.765 --> 53:44.974
You don't need to worry.

53:45.016 --> 53:46.518
Don't worry?

53:46.559 --> 53:48.353
-Dad, we need to act fast--
-HAL: Elisha.

53:49.562 --> 53:50.689
I said I'm handling it.

53:56.569 --> 53:59.322
You need to focus on your work.

53:59.364 --> 54:03.326
You know, I was thinking
why don't you pitch

54:03.368 --> 54:05.954
-Nicholas Booker about a column?
-Dad! Dad! Mom!

54:08.373 --> 54:11.418
Look. I've been talking
about cancer all day.

54:11.459 --> 54:13.420
-LYNN: Hal.
-I'm sick of it.

54:29.978 --> 54:32.439
Nick and I are working
on something really big, dad.

54:34.816 --> 54:35.775
That's good.

54:35.817 --> 54:36.776
ELI:
Yeah.

54:36.818 --> 54:40.780
(***)

54:42.824 --> 54:44.868
[sobs, sniffles]

54:48.663 --> 54:49.706
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Hey, babe.

54:50.957 --> 54:50.999
My plane's about to take off.
What's up?

54:54.502 --> 54:55.670
Eli, can-- can you hear me?

54:57.505 --> 54:58.965
[stewardess speaking
indistinctly]

54:59.007 --> 54:59.883
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Oh, shit.

55:01.468 --> 55:03.970
Eli? Is everything all right?

55:04.012 --> 55:04.971
It's my dad.

55:06.514 --> 55:08.350
He's sick.

55:08.391 --> 55:10.643
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Sick? How sick?

55:11.353 --> 55:12.062
STEWARDESS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Sir.

55:13.146 --> 55:13.646
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Oh, shit.

55:15.106 --> 55:15.148
Listen. I'm gonna catch
the first flight back, okay?

55:15.815 --> 55:15.857
No! No, no, no, no.

55:17.233 --> 55:19.736
We're taking care of it.
You're where you need to be.

55:21.029 --> 55:21.905
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Okay.

55:23.114 --> 55:24.032
I love you.

55:25.492 --> 55:27.118
I love you, too, babe.

55:28.870 --> 55:28.912
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Eli, I'm gonna lose you
until we land.

55:30.121 --> 55:30.163
I'm calling you back
as soon as I can.

55:30.538 --> 55:33.792
[sobs]

55:33.833 --> 55:42.759
(***)

55:58.149 --> 55:59.776
Who's your source?

55:59.818 --> 56:01.444
Jennifer Cooke in PR.

56:03.154 --> 56:04.406
Let's get to work.

56:04.447 --> 56:08.410
(***)

56:12.706 --> 56:15.834
CORRESPONDENT 9 (ON TV):
As summer fades to fall,
the race has never been tighter.

56:15.875 --> 56:17.002
CORRESPONDENT 10 (ON TV):
I mean, the man's trying

56:18.336 --> 56:19.421
to do something
that's never been done before.

56:20.839 --> 56:20.964
And I'm just not convinced
that he can pull it off.

56:22.132 --> 56:22.173
CORRESPONDENT 11 (ON TV):
Whoa! Hold on.

56:23.383 --> 56:24.592
He sold out the big house
in Michigan.

56:25.593 --> 56:28.138
That's a 110,000
for a political rally.

56:28.179 --> 56:29.889
I've never seen anything
like it.

56:29.931 --> 56:31.599
CORRESPONDENT 12 (ON TV):
Okay. I mean, it is impressive.

56:31.641 --> 56:33.143
But it's not like
Senator Turnbull's just

56:33.184 --> 56:34.102
gonna roll over.

56:35.186 --> 56:36.438
She's had the lead
since day one.

56:37.522 --> 56:37.605
REPORTER (ON TV):
Who do you plan to vote for?

56:38.690 --> 56:39.482
YOUNG VOTER (ON TV):
Nate Sterling.

56:41.192 --> 56:41.651
REPORTER (ON TV):
Do you usually vote Democrat
or Republican?

56:42.902 --> 56:42.944
YOUNG VOTER (ON TV):
I've never voted before.

56:44.029 --> 56:44.070
And this is my first time
voting.

56:44.612 --> 56:47.991
(***)

56:50.160 --> 56:51.786
[sighs]

57:20.815 --> 57:21.983
Nick.

57:22.025 --> 57:22.984
Huh?

57:24.152 --> 57:24.944
ELI:
Does it make any sense

57:25.862 --> 57:26.988
for the director
of SuperMillions

57:28.239 --> 57:29.532
to send an expense report
for a holiday party

57:29.574 --> 57:32.535
to a partner
at Meyers & Goldstein?

57:32.577 --> 57:34.537
No.

57:34.579 --> 57:37.499
An assistant would perform
those menial tasks. Why?

57:55.183 --> 57:56.685
I think these invoices
are fakes.

57:58.728 --> 58:01.231
They each contain
a four, an eight, or both.

58:01.272 --> 58:02.023
That's the tell.

58:02.565 --> 58:03.983
Well, it's human nature

58:04.025 --> 58:05.985
to prefer some numbers
over others.

58:06.027 --> 58:08.697
This is how companies spot
expense-account fraud.

58:08.738 --> 58:11.741
I mean, I'm willing to bet
that the Memorial Day retreat

58:11.783 --> 58:12.701
didn't even happen.

58:12.742 --> 58:13.868
NICK:
Well, any real invoices

58:13.910 --> 58:15.161
from Patriot Catering

58:15.203 --> 58:17.789
sure didn't pass
through these execs.

58:21.251 --> 58:25.213
ELI:
174684.

58:28.216 --> 58:37.142
(***)

58:40.895 --> 58:44.858
The average SuperMillions
jackpot is $20 million.

58:44.899 --> 58:48.028
In recessions, jackpots
increase by approximately

58:48.069 --> 58:49.863
eight percent.

58:49.904 --> 58:52.073
So, that means
that the average jackpot

58:52.115 --> 58:54.117
-should be...
-21.6 million.

58:55.368 --> 58:58.163
Correct. 21.6 million.

58:58.204 --> 59:02.709
But it's holding steady
at 19 million.

59:02.751 --> 59:05.712
Well, that's a gap
of 2.6 million per drawing.

59:09.674 --> 59:12.093
ELI:
Right. The first
Patriot trading invoice

59:12.135 --> 59:16.056
goes back to 34 weeks ago.

59:17.724 --> 59:19.392
Two drawings a week. That's...

59:19.434 --> 59:20.352
ELI:
That is...

59:23.355 --> 59:24.314
God.

59:27.609 --> 59:30.362
-Pretty damn close to bulls-eye.
-Holy fuck.

59:31.696 --> 59:34.949
For every $1,000 embezzled

59:34.991 --> 59:36.076
from the SuperMillions lottery

59:37.285 --> 59:38.370
and transferred to UpRight,
the invoice...

59:38.411 --> 59:40.038
Show a buck.

59:40.080 --> 59:40.955
Yeah.

59:40.997 --> 59:42.916
That's their fucking code.

59:44.793 --> 59:45.335
[sighs]

59:45.377 --> 59:46.419
ELI:
Erickson.

59:46.461 --> 59:49.756
Erickson fudges the books, okay?

59:49.798 --> 59:52.717
The money moves
in the dark of night.

59:52.759 --> 59:56.971
The-- the-- the-- the invoices
track the spoils,

59:57.013 --> 1:00:00.266
letting them communicate
without having to type fraud

1:00:00.308 --> 1:00:01.685
in the subject line.

1:00:01.726 --> 1:00:02.769
[Nick chuckles]

1:00:02.811 --> 1:00:04.229
A barn full of haystacks.

1:00:05.730 --> 1:00:08.358
And you found
the fucking needle.

1:00:08.400 --> 1:00:09.693
[chuckles softly]

1:00:09.734 --> 1:00:10.276
[indistinct chatter]

1:00:11.069 --> 1:00:11.152
COLLEGE KID:
Thank you.

1:00:11.695 --> 1:00:20.161
(***)

1:00:23.832 --> 1:00:26.292
Hey, can I bum a cigarette?

1:00:26.334 --> 1:00:27.293
COLLEGE KID:
Oh, yeah.

1:00:30.338 --> 1:00:31.297
ELI:
Thanks.

1:00:31.339 --> 1:00:33.091
Oh, so, you're the caterer.

1:00:33.133 --> 1:00:34.801
-COLLEGE KID: Yeah.
-Excellent job inside.

1:00:34.843 --> 1:00:36.720
Those deviled eggs
look delicious.

1:00:36.761 --> 1:00:37.846
COLLEGE KID:
Thanks.

1:00:38.722 --> 1:00:38.805
I wish I could tell you
that I made them,

1:00:39.931 --> 1:00:41.016
but I just load 'em in
and hand 'em out.

1:00:41.057 --> 1:00:42.475
[exhales]

1:00:42.517 --> 1:00:44.728
"Patriot Catering." [chuckles]

1:00:44.769 --> 1:00:46.855
-COLLEGE KID: That's us.
-Haven't seen you guys before.

1:00:46.896 --> 1:00:47.939
Have you been in business
for a long time?

1:00:47.981 --> 1:00:50.150
Uh, coming up to a year.

1:00:50.191 --> 1:00:52.193
-ELI: Wow. Really new.
-Mm-hmm.

1:00:52.235 --> 1:00:53.987
-ELI: Family-owned?
-Nope.

1:00:54.029 --> 1:00:55.905
This dude named Dean owns it.

1:00:55.947 --> 1:00:57.991
Wait. Not Dean Bender.

1:00:58.033 --> 1:01:00.744
No. Dean Clifton.

1:01:00.785 --> 1:01:03.079
Oh, gotcha. Clifton.

1:01:03.121 --> 1:01:04.247
Yeah.

1:01:04.289 --> 1:01:06.082
So, you got a lot of events
coming up?

1:01:06.124 --> 1:01:08.752
-Rubbing elbows with D.C.
big wigs?
-[college kid chuckles]

1:01:08.793 --> 1:01:10.170
COLLEGE KID:
We got some big ones coming up.

1:01:11.713 --> 1:01:12.964
But honestly, they're, like,
all the same to me, you know?

1:01:13.006 --> 1:01:15.884
Same bacon-wrapped scallops.
Same penguin suit.

1:01:15.925 --> 1:01:17.802
Same rich folks
boring up the place.

1:01:17.844 --> 1:01:20.513
[chuckles]

1:01:20.555 --> 1:01:22.098
You got a card?

1:01:22.140 --> 1:01:23.850
COLLEGE KID:
Oh, yeah.

1:01:23.892 --> 1:01:26.853
Just you know, somewhere here.

1:01:26.895 --> 1:01:29.064
Here.
Uh, the menu's in that link.

1:01:30.440 --> 1:01:32.776
So, if you ever throw a bash,
you know, we're around.

1:01:33.526 --> 1:01:35.070
Cool. Thanks.

1:01:35.111 --> 1:01:36.279
-Yeah.
-And thanks.

1:01:36.321 --> 1:01:38.239
-Yeah. Have a good one.
-You, too.

1:01:42.327 --> 1:01:43.953
MODERATOR:
Thank you.
Thank you, Mr. President.

1:01:43.995 --> 1:01:46.122
We need to move on,
and I wanna give

1:01:46.164 --> 1:01:49.417
Mr. Sterling a chance to
respond
before closing statements.

1:01:49.459 --> 1:01:51.002
Let's face it.

1:01:51.044 --> 1:01:52.879
Washington's got one foot
so far left

1:01:52.921 --> 1:01:56.216
and the other so far right,
that it can't stand up straight.

1:01:56.257 --> 1:01:58.468
Congress is doing a split
in the quicksand,

1:01:58.510 --> 1:01:59.969
and I'm the only guy
that can pull us out

1:02:00.011 --> 1:02:01.137
of this partisan quagmire.

1:02:01.179 --> 1:02:04.057
Why?
Because I'm free.

1:02:04.099 --> 1:02:06.935
Free of special interests.
Free of party-power brokers.

1:02:06.976 --> 1:02:09.396
And I'm free to explore
the best ideas

1:02:09.437 --> 1:02:11.147
from both sides of the aisle.

1:02:11.189 --> 1:02:13.024
Because I don't sit
on either one.

1:02:13.066 --> 1:02:14.109
I stand proudly in the middle.

1:02:17.070 --> 1:02:18.238
Credentials to the debate?

1:02:20.949 --> 1:02:21.866
TURNBULL (ON TV):
Sure.

1:02:23.118 --> 1:02:24.953
What's it being Booker's
lapdog,
eh?

1:02:26.955 --> 1:02:28.415
[barks]

1:02:28.456 --> 1:02:30.041
TURNBULL:
But what you don't seem
to understand, sir,

1:02:30.083 --> 1:02:31.835
we're talking about decisions

1:02:31.876 --> 1:02:34.004
that can mean the difference
between life and death.

1:02:34.045 --> 1:02:35.922
-The wisdom...
-Tell me the truth, though.

1:02:35.964 --> 1:02:39.175
Has, um...
has the old man lost a step?

1:02:41.052 --> 1:02:42.971
You know, just putting
so much time

1:02:43.013 --> 1:02:45.515
into a cub with a rap sheet.

1:02:47.183 --> 1:02:49.561
If I were you, I would just
keep
asking myself why?

1:02:50.937 --> 1:02:53.106
I'm trying to watch the debate.

1:02:53.148 --> 1:02:55.275
Take it easy, Patricia.

1:02:55.316 --> 1:02:57.444
Mr. Sterling represented
our country proudly.

1:02:57.485 --> 1:02:58.862
TURNBULL:
Oh, oh, oh.

1:02:58.903 --> 1:03:00.572
I beg your pardon,
Mr. President.

1:03:00.613 --> 1:03:03.074
The only reason you're giving
his lack of experience

1:03:03.116 --> 1:03:05.910
a hall pass is because you see
in the polls

1:03:05.952 --> 1:03:08.872
that he's gonna steal more
votes
from me than he is from you

1:03:08.913 --> 1:03:10.874
in key battleground states.

1:03:10.915 --> 1:03:14.836
But this election
is about so much more

1:03:14.878 --> 1:03:15.837
than politics.

1:03:17.088 --> 1:03:19.299
And I'm not even talking
about what it'll mean

1:03:19.341 --> 1:03:23.178
to millions of little girls
to see a woman take

1:03:23.219 --> 1:03:25.930
the oath of office
for the very first time

1:03:25.972 --> 1:03:27.223
in this country.

1:03:27.265 --> 1:03:30.018
That's significant. Oh!

1:03:30.060 --> 1:03:31.978
Yes, it is.

1:03:32.020 --> 1:03:34.397
But let's leave that discussion
to the history books,

1:03:34.439 --> 1:03:36.024
'cause what I wanna talk
about right now

1:03:37.400 --> 1:03:39.277
is what my administration
is gonna do

1:03:39.319 --> 1:03:42.530
to make your lives better.
Plain simple.

1:03:42.572 --> 1:03:45.033
Like fixing that pothole
on your street.

1:03:45.075 --> 1:03:48.328
Getting your 401K moving up
and to the right again.

1:03:48.370 --> 1:03:50.663
Keeping you
and your children safe

1:03:50.705 --> 1:03:52.624
from enemies,
foreign and domestic.

1:03:52.665 --> 1:03:55.377
Pulling us out of this
recession
once and for all.

1:03:56.503 --> 1:04:00.006
And most importantly,
shining a light

1:04:00.048 --> 1:04:03.009
on the working people
of this country

1:04:03.051 --> 1:04:05.595
who have been invisible
for far too long.

1:04:07.097 --> 1:04:09.057
That's what
I'm gonna talk about.

1:04:09.099 --> 1:04:10.892
[crowd cheering, whistling]

1:04:10.934 --> 1:04:11.893
Thank you.

1:04:13.144 --> 1:04:14.562
What will it mean

1:04:14.604 --> 1:04:17.232
for millions of little girls
to see a female president?

1:04:19.234 --> 1:04:20.402
Far more than I could ever
comprehend.

1:04:21.986 --> 1:04:24.364
But what's it gonna mean
for our environment,

1:04:24.406 --> 1:04:28.284
for our teachers,
for our poor and middle class

1:04:28.326 --> 1:04:30.286
to see you as president,
Senator Turnbull?

1:04:31.955 --> 1:04:34.332
We are long overdue for a woman
in the White House.

1:04:34.374 --> 1:04:36.459
But it can't just be any woman.

1:04:36.501 --> 1:04:38.420
It's gotta be the right woman.

1:04:38.461 --> 1:04:39.963
Not a woman that denied
climate change

1:04:40.005 --> 1:04:41.256
is real till just last year.

1:04:43.925 --> 1:04:45.510
And that is precisely
why my cabinet

1:04:45.552 --> 1:04:47.012
will be made up
of 50 percent women

1:04:47.053 --> 1:04:47.971
at the very minimal.

1:04:48.013 --> 1:04:50.140
[crowd cheering]

1:04:53.018 --> 1:04:55.061
[indistinct chatter]

1:04:55.103 --> 1:04:57.022
-You look nice.
-LUCAS: Thanks.

1:04:57.063 --> 1:04:58.940
I can't believe we're actually
in the same state.

1:04:58.982 --> 1:05:00.358
I kinda like it.

1:05:00.400 --> 1:05:02.193
Think you might wanna ditch
your credentials.

1:05:02.235 --> 1:05:04.404
You'll scare the personality
out of everyone.

1:05:04.446 --> 1:05:06.197
Hey, Nate.

1:05:06.239 --> 1:05:07.449
-Awesome job.
-[Nate chuckles]

1:05:07.490 --> 1:05:09.242
Thank you.
What are the mosquitos sayin'?

1:05:09.284 --> 1:05:11.327
Well, most of the pundits
are calling it for you,

1:05:11.369 --> 1:05:13.246
and Twitter's looking
pretty bullish.

1:05:13.288 --> 1:05:15.081
You remember my girlfriend,
Eli.

1:05:15.123 --> 1:05:16.499
[chuckles]
That I do.

1:05:18.168 --> 1:05:20.003
I hear you're making big waves
over at the Chronicle.

1:05:20.045 --> 1:05:21.129
[chuckles]

1:05:21.171 --> 1:05:23.340
Splashing about
in the shallow end,

1:05:23.381 --> 1:05:25.050
but I'm trying.

1:05:25.091 --> 1:05:25.967
NATE:
I'm sure you had to disclose

1:05:27.052 --> 1:05:27.385
that you're dating
this handsome guy.

1:05:27.427 --> 1:05:28.720
I did.

1:05:28.762 --> 1:05:30.638
But it helps that I'm not
covering your campaign.

1:05:31.973 --> 1:05:32.932
NATE:
Of course.

1:05:32.974 --> 1:05:33.683
What did you think
of the debate?

1:05:35.143 --> 1:05:36.144
Honestly?

1:05:37.437 --> 1:05:38.772
I'd be surprised
if you didn't poach

1:05:38.813 --> 1:05:40.398
a point or two
from both parties.

1:05:42.359 --> 1:05:43.401
-She's a keeper.
-LUCAS: Hmm.

1:05:43.443 --> 1:05:44.986
And you, miss,

1:05:45.028 --> 1:05:46.488
you are lucky to have a guy
like this by your side.

1:05:47.322 --> 1:05:48.615
As are you.

1:05:50.075 --> 1:05:50.408
Speaking of which, Lucas,
can I steal you for a second?

1:05:51.451 --> 1:05:51.493
There's somebody
I want you to meet.

1:05:51.951 --> 1:05:52.494
Thank you.

1:05:58.041 --> 1:05:58.500
LUCAS:
Hey.

1:05:59.167 --> 1:06:00.710
[indistinct chatter]

1:06:04.673 --> 1:06:05.715
COLLEGE KID:
May I take these?

1:06:07.509 --> 1:06:09.511
Hey. Patriot Catering?

1:06:09.552 --> 1:06:11.388
[chuckles] I'll be damned.

1:06:11.429 --> 1:06:12.597
-[Eli chuckles]
-How goes it?

1:06:12.639 --> 1:06:14.140
[Eli gasps]

1:06:14.182 --> 1:06:15.642
-Wait. This is the big event?
-COLLEGE KID: Yeah.

1:06:15.684 --> 1:06:18.311
The most exciting night
of your life, right?

1:06:18.353 --> 1:06:19.521
So boring.

1:06:19.562 --> 1:06:21.648
You might just be serving
the next president

1:06:21.690 --> 1:06:23.149
of the United States of America.

1:06:23.775 --> 1:06:25.360
That dude?

1:06:25.402 --> 1:06:27.028
We've been catering for him
since before he entered

1:06:27.070 --> 1:06:27.737
the race.

1:06:27.779 --> 1:06:29.030
The lustre's worn off.

1:06:30.031 --> 1:06:31.074
Plus, the boss doesn't want me
to spread around.

1:06:32.742 --> 1:06:34.494
Makes sense.

1:06:34.536 --> 1:06:36.705
I mean, you probably do
business
with the Republicans, too.

1:06:36.746 --> 1:06:38.164
No, just Sterling.

1:06:38.206 --> 1:06:39.374
Dean's loyal like that.

1:06:39.416 --> 1:06:41.418
I should probably get back
to work.

1:06:41.459 --> 1:06:43.503
He likes us to move around.

1:06:43.545 --> 1:06:45.463
-Dean is here?
-Yeah.

1:06:45.505 --> 1:06:48.508
Talking to Sterling
and Jack Hampton.

1:06:48.550 --> 1:06:50.719
He's looking over here.
I better keep moving.

1:06:54.180 --> 1:06:55.390
I'll see you at the next one.

1:06:57.809 --> 1:07:00.687
-MAYFIELD: Hey! Gentlemen!
-NATE: Hey! How are you, sir?

1:07:02.439 --> 1:07:03.356
-Tom Mayfield.
-LUCAS: I'm Lucas.

1:07:03.398 --> 1:07:04.274
Nice to meet you.

1:07:04.315 --> 1:07:08.236
(***)

1:07:12.198 --> 1:07:13.575
LUCAS:
Hey.

1:07:13.616 --> 1:07:16.453
That was the owner
of your paper.

1:07:16.494 --> 1:07:18.329
Don't worry.
I didn't embarrass you.

1:07:18.371 --> 1:07:19.330
Who else is there?

1:07:20.582 --> 1:07:21.583
Bunch of big donors.

1:07:22.792 --> 1:07:24.252
The guy on the right
owns a slew

1:07:24.294 --> 1:07:25.754
of catering companies.

1:07:25.795 --> 1:07:29.299
Nate says that he is
a culinary mastermind.

1:07:29.341 --> 1:07:30.550
What's his name?

1:07:30.592 --> 1:07:32.302
Uh, Dean something.

1:07:32.344 --> 1:07:33.428
Everyone calls him "The Chef."

1:07:34.804 --> 1:07:36.806
-I gotta go.
-Hey. What? We just got here.

1:07:36.848 --> 1:07:38.683
Lucas, I gotta go.

1:07:38.725 --> 1:07:40.268
I haven't seen you in weeks
and you're leaving?

1:07:40.310 --> 1:07:41.311
Eli!

1:07:41.353 --> 1:07:50.320
(***)

1:07:59.371 --> 1:08:08.338
(***)

1:08:18.765 --> 1:08:19.766
How was it?

1:08:19.808 --> 1:08:21.601
ELI:
Nick, we need to talk.

1:08:21.643 --> 1:08:24.270
Turnbull isn't embezzling money
from SuperMillions.

1:08:24.312 --> 1:08:25.313
Sterling is.

1:08:27.148 --> 1:08:28.233
You think that's funny?

1:08:28.274 --> 1:08:29.317
ELI:
No, I'm serious.

1:08:30.819 --> 1:08:33.780
Patriot Catering worked
his debate afterparty.

1:08:33.822 --> 1:08:36.366
They have catered
all of Sterling's events

1:08:36.408 --> 1:08:38.618
since before he entered
the race.

1:08:38.660 --> 1:08:40.870
It was right in front
of our faces the whole time.

1:08:40.912 --> 1:08:42.580
Meyers & Goldstein,
they handled the books

1:08:42.622 --> 1:08:43.957
for Sterling's Super PAC
as well.

1:08:43.998 --> 1:08:46.292
Sterling reject
the Super PAC on principle.

1:08:46.334 --> 1:08:47.669
ELI:
In the first month
of his campaign,

1:08:47.711 --> 1:08:48.628
he made a big show of it.

1:08:48.670 --> 1:08:49.879
But that did not last long.

1:08:53.174 --> 1:08:54.968
NICK:
Integrity Super PAC?
[scoffs]

1:08:55.010 --> 1:08:56.594
That's an oxymoron.

1:08:57.846 --> 1:08:58.638
Yeah. He named it something
generic to keep a low profile--

1:09:00.098 --> 1:09:01.224
Yeah. Still, still, still,
this isn't definitive proof

1:09:01.266 --> 1:09:03.518
that he--
Why would he be that bold?

1:09:03.560 --> 1:09:06.312
Juice isn't worth the squeeze.
He's up three points.

1:09:06.354 --> 1:09:07.564
He is now.

1:09:07.605 --> 1:09:08.815
But this time last year,
his name

1:09:08.857 --> 1:09:10.191
wasn't on a single poll.

1:09:11.526 --> 1:09:13.236
What's the only way to win
the New York City Marathon

1:09:13.278 --> 1:09:14.195
without any training?

1:09:15.321 --> 1:09:17.574
Take the subway,
sneak under the rope

1:09:17.615 --> 1:09:18.950
-on mile 18.
-On mile 18.

1:09:21.494 --> 1:09:24.581
But Mayfield,
that bow-tied prick.

1:09:24.622 --> 1:09:27.250
I mean, he's a Republican.
It doesn't make any sense.

1:09:27.292 --> 1:09:28.501
I thought the same thing.

1:09:28.543 --> 1:09:30.754
So, I checked out
his voting records.

1:09:30.795 --> 1:09:33.381
And it turns out,
he left the Republican Party

1:09:33.423 --> 1:09:36.009
right after Reagan rode off
into the sunset.

1:09:36.051 --> 1:09:38.720
The man has been an independent
for the last three decades.

1:09:38.762 --> 1:09:41.514
And then he reregistered
as a Republican the same month

1:09:41.556 --> 1:09:43.516
that Sterling's book
hit the best-seller list.

1:09:43.558 --> 1:09:45.643
It was all calculated.

1:09:45.685 --> 1:09:46.895
He must have thought
if people like us picked up

1:09:48.229 --> 1:09:48.605
a scent, it would throw us
off the trail, and...

1:09:49.939 --> 1:09:50.899
it worked.

1:09:52.400 --> 1:09:53.985
What the fuck do we do now?

1:09:57.405 --> 1:09:58.948
Follow the facts
wherever they lead.

1:10:00.283 --> 1:10:01.534
Sometimes,
it's not where you wanna go,

1:10:01.576 --> 1:10:02.827
but you go anyway.

1:10:06.915 --> 1:10:08.291
[sighs]

1:10:08.333 --> 1:10:09.834
CORRESPONDENT 13 (ON TV):
With just one week to go,

1:10:11.086 --> 1:10:12.545
Nate Sterling has pulled ahead
of Senator Turnbull

1:10:13.588 --> 1:10:15.256
for the first time
in national polling.

1:10:16.591 --> 1:10:17.884
While the lead is still
within the margin of error...

1:10:17.926 --> 1:10:19.969
Sterling is our megaphone,

1:10:20.011 --> 1:10:22.889
our voice of reason,
our moral compass,

1:10:22.931 --> 1:10:24.599
and our hope
for a better tomorrow.

1:10:31.314 --> 1:10:32.273
Shit, Eli.

1:10:33.650 --> 1:10:34.651
Where did you run off to?

1:10:37.779 --> 1:10:38.780
What's wrong?

1:10:42.283 --> 1:10:43.034
You see your dad?

1:10:45.286 --> 1:10:47.455
-You're gonna have to scrap
that speech.
-Why? The town hall's tomorrow--

1:10:47.497 --> 1:10:48.707
Because you're not a liar.

1:10:48.748 --> 1:10:50.458
What are you talking about?

1:10:50.500 --> 1:10:52.752
-He's funding his campaign
with stolen money.
-What? Who?

1:10:52.794 --> 1:10:54.337
Sterling.

1:10:54.379 --> 1:10:56.297
-What are you saying?
-I have hard evidence.

1:10:56.339 --> 1:10:59.718
He's embezzling money
from the lottery,

1:10:59.759 --> 1:11:00.927
and funneling
it to his Super PAC.

1:11:00.969 --> 1:11:02.679
What? That's crazy.

1:11:02.721 --> 1:11:03.972
It's the truth.

1:11:04.014 --> 1:11:05.056
Nick and I have been working
this story--

1:11:05.098 --> 1:11:07.684
No. Why are you telling me this?

1:11:07.726 --> 1:11:09.019
I guess I thought

1:11:09.060 --> 1:11:10.061
you might like to know
that your hero is a fraud.

1:11:10.103 --> 1:11:11.730
Hey. Stop!

1:11:11.771 --> 1:11:13.732
ELI:
And because I need your help.

1:11:13.773 --> 1:11:15.775
Are you--
are you listening to yourself?

1:11:15.817 --> 1:11:18.653
I need someone on the inside
to prove he signed off on it.

1:11:20.488 --> 1:11:21.865
Here.

1:11:21.906 --> 1:11:23.658
I need you to fill this
with Sterling's hard drive.

1:11:23.700 --> 1:11:25.368
-We don't have much time.
-LUCAS: You're delusional.

1:11:25.410 --> 1:11:26.494
ELI:
Goddammit, Lucas!

1:11:26.536 --> 1:11:28.038
You're in denial.

1:11:28.079 --> 1:11:29.831
LUCAS:
No. You can't fucking
help yourself, can you?

1:11:29.873 --> 1:11:31.791
Only this time,
when you blow yourself up,

1:11:31.833 --> 1:11:33.626
you could take me
and the whole goddamn country

1:11:33.668 --> 1:11:34.794
-down with you.
-No. This is different.

1:11:34.836 --> 1:11:35.837
This is real.

1:11:37.005 --> 1:11:38.840
Okay. Let's say that it is real.

1:11:40.967 --> 1:11:42.635
You go from reporting
back-page news

1:11:42.677 --> 1:11:44.346
to being front-page news.

1:11:45.430 --> 1:11:46.931
I get what?

1:11:46.973 --> 1:11:49.768
A seat on the witness stand
in the trial of the century

1:11:49.809 --> 1:11:51.019
when the only thing
I have witnessed

1:11:51.061 --> 1:11:53.355
is a good man
trying to save his country.

1:11:54.731 --> 1:11:56.483
We get hate mails
from our friends,

1:11:56.524 --> 1:11:57.484
the people we respect.

1:11:57.525 --> 1:11:58.651
And then what?

1:11:59.569 --> 1:12:01.571
Gun-toting, gay-bashing,
autocratic zealots,

1:12:01.613 --> 1:12:04.074
they declare us heroes,
and the navel-gazing,

1:12:04.115 --> 1:12:05.992
holier-than-thou woke mob,
they throw us

1:12:06.034 --> 1:12:06.910
a fucking parade,

1:12:07.952 --> 1:12:08.578
congratulations
to the both of us?

1:12:09.829 --> 1:12:10.080
ELI:
Lucas, please calm down.
And just think--

1:12:10.622 --> 1:12:11.498
No, you think!

1:12:15.543 --> 1:12:18.672
Are you willing to keep Penny
at war for the next ten years?

1:12:18.713 --> 1:12:21.966
No. Are you willing to sit
on your hands

1:12:22.008 --> 1:12:24.386
while the fucking Earth fries,
because I'm not.

1:12:24.427 --> 1:12:26.680
The money that he is stealing

1:12:26.721 --> 1:12:28.056
is coming from schools,
like that one in--

1:12:28.098 --> 1:12:29.808
that one in West Virginia.

1:12:29.849 --> 1:12:31.935
Okay? Those kids,
Black and brown kids

1:12:31.976 --> 1:12:33.019
are losing access to a fair
and equal education.

1:12:33.061 --> 1:12:35.021
Eli, it is so much bigger than--

1:12:35.063 --> 1:12:37.107
Don't you fucking finish
that thought!

1:12:39.401 --> 1:12:40.151
Why doesn't this matter to you?

1:12:40.193 --> 1:12:41.903
They matter!

1:12:41.945 --> 1:12:43.196
Everyone else in this country
can act like they don't exist--

1:12:43.238 --> 1:12:45.156
LUCAS:
He is what this country needs!

1:12:45.198 --> 1:12:47.575
A liar is the last thing
this country needs!

1:12:48.743 --> 1:12:50.120
Liars are what fucked
this country up

1:12:50.161 --> 1:12:51.162
in the first place.

1:12:52.914 --> 1:12:55.709
Iraq has stockpiles of WMDs.

1:12:55.750 --> 1:12:57.585
The housing market
will continue to rise.

1:12:57.627 --> 1:12:59.754
The election was rigged.
Redlining.

1:13:01.172 --> 1:13:03.174
The war on drugs,
voter suppression!

1:13:04.843 --> 1:13:08.138
Everywhere you look, lobbyists,
pundits, bankers, preachers,

1:13:08.179 --> 1:13:11.433
billion-dollar industries
that run on lies.

1:13:11.474 --> 1:13:12.809
LUCAS:
What is it that you want, Eli?

1:13:12.851 --> 1:13:14.894
-I want-- I want the truth.
-LUCAS: Yeah.

1:13:14.936 --> 1:13:16.521
Well, you've been duped before,
so.

1:13:17.939 --> 1:13:18.982
[sighs]

1:13:23.236 --> 1:13:24.904
Did you know, Lucas?

1:13:28.158 --> 1:13:29.701
I can't believe
you would even think that.

1:13:31.661 --> 1:13:32.996
[exhales shakily]

1:13:35.123 --> 1:13:37.876
I'm publishing this story
with or without your help.

1:13:41.880 --> 1:13:42.839
You publish this story,

1:13:43.965 --> 1:13:44.591
I don't want anything
to do with you.

1:13:45.884 --> 1:13:46.134
-That is not fair.
-What do you want me to say?

1:13:47.635 --> 1:13:48.678
Love fades, values don't.

1:13:48.720 --> 1:13:57.645
(***)

1:13:59.647 --> 1:14:01.191
That's my fucking jacket!

1:14:01.232 --> 1:14:05.153
(***)

1:14:06.529 --> 1:14:07.489
LUCAS:
Nice.

1:14:07.530 --> 1:14:11.493
(***)

1:14:13.912 --> 1:14:14.913
[sighs]

1:14:14.954 --> 1:14:23.880
(***)

1:14:31.638 --> 1:14:32.597
Meet me at Recessions.

1:14:34.057 --> 1:14:35.850
Two blocks northwest
of Farragut Square.

1:14:37.227 --> 1:14:38.186
I have something.

1:14:39.312 --> 1:14:40.814
[indistinct chatter]

1:14:44.859 --> 1:14:46.653
We prove that Sterling knew.

1:14:46.695 --> 1:14:47.821
-NICK: Eli.
-ELI: I'm going tonight.

1:14:47.862 --> 1:14:49.656
Well, Jesus Christ, Eli.

1:14:49.698 --> 1:14:51.074
You're being irrational.

1:14:51.116 --> 1:14:52.742
There's a right way
and a wrong way.

1:14:52.784 --> 1:14:54.577
If you want the ribeye,
you go get the ribeye.

1:14:54.619 --> 1:14:55.995
Not if it's contaminated.

1:14:56.037 --> 1:14:57.956
That ends a career
before it starts.

1:14:57.997 --> 1:14:59.708
Well, already lost
my relationship.

1:14:59.749 --> 1:15:01.001
I'm losing my dad.

1:15:01.042 --> 1:15:02.836
So, why not throw in a career
for good measure?

1:15:02.877 --> 1:15:04.212
You're losing your mind
is what you're losing.

1:15:05.255 --> 1:15:06.214
Wait.

1:15:07.257 --> 1:15:08.216
Relationship?

1:15:09.926 --> 1:15:10.885
Lucas refuses to--

1:15:10.927 --> 1:15:12.846
Oh, fuck, Eli!

1:15:12.887 --> 1:15:14.097
You told him?

1:15:14.139 --> 1:15:15.390
[sighs]

1:15:15.432 --> 1:15:18.143
They'll have the place
power-cleaned in an hour.

1:15:18.184 --> 1:15:20.645
Shit! Shit!

1:15:20.687 --> 1:15:21.646
You're right.

1:15:21.688 --> 1:15:25.650
(***)

1:15:28.653 --> 1:15:29.863
Eli! Shit!

1:15:31.656 --> 1:15:32.615
Fuck.

1:15:33.742 --> 1:15:34.284
Hello?

1:15:35.035 --> 1:15:36.703
Eli. Wait. Who is this?

1:15:36.745 --> 1:15:37.912
-Nick, put Eli on.
-Hang on.

1:15:41.041 --> 1:15:44.586
Just talk to Eli.
I'm sorry, Lucas.

1:15:44.627 --> 1:15:46.046
She just doesn't wanna talk
to you.

1:15:46.087 --> 1:15:46.963
Where are you?

1:15:48.006 --> 1:15:49.215
We're at Recessions
on 18th and L.

1:15:49.257 --> 1:15:50.050
LUCAS:
Bullshit!

1:15:50.717 --> 1:15:51.217
You're at the campaign office.

1:15:51.259 --> 1:15:52.385
I'm on my way.

1:15:52.427 --> 1:15:53.887
Don't do anything stupid.

1:15:53.928 --> 1:15:56.181
They sing karaoke this good
at the campaign?

1:15:56.222 --> 1:15:58.641
[indiscernible singing]

1:15:59.934 --> 1:16:01.227
Shit! All right.

1:16:01.269 --> 1:16:03.021
Just tell her to stay
right there.

1:16:03.063 --> 1:16:05.732
(***)

1:16:09.652 --> 1:16:18.620
(***)

1:16:27.671 --> 1:16:36.638
(***)

1:16:45.689 --> 1:16:49.651
(***)

1:16:49.693 --> 1:16:50.652
ELI:
Shit!

1:16:50.694 --> 1:16:53.947
(***)

1:16:56.408 --> 1:16:58.785
What the hell
are you doing here?

1:16:58.827 --> 1:17:02.122
-It's past midnight.
Lucas isn't--
-I have numbers, emails, names.

1:17:02.163 --> 1:17:03.957
[scoffs] Sorry, what?

1:17:03.998 --> 1:17:08.128
Tom Mayfield, Spencer Erickson,
Dean Clifton, Patriot Catering.

1:17:08.169 --> 1:17:11.047
I have concrete evidence
of all parties involved.

1:17:11.089 --> 1:17:12.048
You give me one good reason

1:17:13.216 --> 1:17:13.383
right now I shouldn't call
Secret Service

1:17:14.092 --> 1:17:14.676
and throw you in jail.

1:17:15.802 --> 1:17:17.012
-We'd be sharing a cell.
- NATE: Bullshit.

1:17:17.053 --> 1:17:18.972
I would think twice
before you call security.

1:17:19.014 --> 1:17:21.474
The story is already written.
It's in the drafts.

1:17:21.516 --> 1:17:24.978
You have me arrested,
it goes on Twitter instantly.

1:17:25.020 --> 1:17:26.813
Newspapers in the morning.

1:17:26.855 --> 1:17:28.273
What's this little story about?

1:17:28.314 --> 1:17:30.108
-You know what it's about.
-Enlighten me.

1:17:30.150 --> 1:17:31.818
ELI:
What it's always about.

1:17:31.860 --> 1:17:32.819
Money.

1:17:35.864 --> 1:17:37.907
-Did you know?
-NATE: Know what?

1:17:37.949 --> 1:17:40.493
All I know is I love my country.

1:17:40.535 --> 1:17:41.745
All right? I'm our best hope.

1:17:42.871 --> 1:17:44.039
I give us a fighting chance.

1:17:47.709 --> 1:17:48.710
Wow.

1:17:48.752 --> 1:17:52.714
(***)

1:17:57.844 --> 1:17:59.262
Are you a patriot, Eli?

1:17:59.304 --> 1:18:02.015
Patriots don't steal
from the American people.

1:18:02.057 --> 1:18:03.475
Who are you to accuse anyone of
stealing,

1:18:03.516 --> 1:18:05.477
you fucking hypocrite?

1:18:05.518 --> 1:18:06.436
Give it to me.

1:18:14.069 --> 1:18:16.029
[sighs]

1:18:16.071 --> 1:18:18.365
You know, I think you and I
have a lot in common, Eli.

1:18:18.406 --> 1:18:20.367
And for one,
we both lack experience.

1:18:20.408 --> 1:18:22.077
Turnbull and Archer are
canaries
with that attack line.

1:18:22.118 --> 1:18:25.038
I'm ahead
in every one of the polls,

1:18:25.080 --> 1:18:28.041
economy, hot buttons,
but the race, still a dead heat.

1:18:28.083 --> 1:18:29.376
Why is that?

1:18:29.417 --> 1:18:31.795
'Cause unfortunately,
for me and for you,

1:18:31.836 --> 1:18:32.837
experience seems to matter.

1:18:34.881 --> 1:18:35.507
The way I see it,

1:18:36.800 --> 1:18:39.052
your story
might cause a little stir.

1:18:39.094 --> 1:18:41.471
When it comes down to it,
who's gonna believe you?

1:18:41.513 --> 1:18:43.390
You lack the most vital asset
a journalist must have,

1:18:43.431 --> 1:18:45.308
credibility.

1:18:45.350 --> 1:18:47.894
Looks like I'm late
to the party.

1:18:47.936 --> 1:18:50.271
-Uh, Mr. Booker.
What a surprise--
-Sit the fuck down.

1:18:51.940 --> 1:18:52.941
Now...

1:18:54.317 --> 1:18:57.320
let us all take a deep breath

1:18:57.362 --> 1:18:59.406
and talk this out

1:18:59.447 --> 1:19:02.242
like the rational people we are.

1:19:02.283 --> 1:19:03.368
Nate, don't say a word.

1:19:03.410 --> 1:19:04.577
Eli records everything
on her phone.

1:19:04.619 --> 1:19:05.995
-What?
-Let me see.

1:19:06.037 --> 1:19:07.163
Get off! It's not on me.

1:19:09.457 --> 1:19:10.792
Hey! No, no. Leave him out.

1:19:11.751 --> 1:19:12.961
-NICK: That won't be necessary.
-NATE: Hey!

1:19:13.003 --> 1:19:13.920
You wanna talk or what?

1:19:21.177 --> 1:19:22.178
What the fuck?

1:19:22.220 --> 1:19:23.805
NATE:
All right.

1:19:23.847 --> 1:19:24.264
All right?

1:19:26.474 --> 1:19:27.434
Let's just take a deep breath.

1:19:29.477 --> 1:19:31.104
Sit down and talk this out,
okay?

1:19:31.146 --> 1:19:33.314
This is obviously some sort
of huge misunderstanding.

1:19:33.356 --> 1:19:34.607
NICK:
We know what you did.

1:19:34.649 --> 1:19:35.817
NATE:
Okay.

1:19:36.651 --> 1:19:36.985
With all due respect,
I have no idea

1:19:37.861 --> 1:19:38.153
what you guys are talking about.

1:19:38.903 --> 1:19:39.237
NICK:
Maybe you don't.

1:19:40.321 --> 1:19:42.032
But right now,
there are two assholes

1:19:42.073 --> 1:19:44.200
saying you do.

1:19:44.242 --> 1:19:46.911
There's no need for us to
bluff.
We don't have a smoking gun.

1:19:46.953 --> 1:19:49.622
But as my esteemed colleague
has no doubt informed you,

1:19:49.664 --> 1:19:51.291
we've got the bullets,
the casings,

1:19:51.332 --> 1:19:54.044
and the goddamn forensic report.

1:19:54.085 --> 1:19:58.631
The whole story tied in a bow,
just waiting for the proof

1:19:58.673 --> 1:20:00.383
that you knew about it.

1:20:01.926 --> 1:20:06.014
If we do decide to print,
you got every news outlet

1:20:06.056 --> 1:20:09.434
in the country
on a scavenger hunt for proof

1:20:10.935 --> 1:20:11.853
of your involvement.

1:20:12.896 --> 1:20:13.355
There is no proof
of my involvement.

1:20:14.939 --> 1:20:16.441
The allegation itself knocks
you
out of the White House.

1:20:16.483 --> 1:20:18.193
You'll spend the next few years
in court.

1:20:19.152 --> 1:20:20.862
And if you did know,

1:20:20.904 --> 1:20:22.572
the next couple of decades
in prison.

1:20:23.948 --> 1:20:27.202
So, the way I see it,
if you want any hope

1:20:27.243 --> 1:20:31.247
of reversing this unfortunate
chain of events,

1:20:31.289 --> 1:20:34.459
you will tell us
the God's honest truth

1:20:34.501 --> 1:20:36.544
right here and now.

1:20:37.587 --> 1:20:38.505
Okay. Uh--

1:20:38.546 --> 1:20:41.383
But before you do,

1:20:43.259 --> 1:20:45.178
a disclaimer.

1:20:45.220 --> 1:20:47.597
I've worked in this town
for 52 years.

1:20:49.057 --> 1:20:52.352
That makes me one
of the world's foremost experts

1:20:52.394 --> 1:20:54.604
at spotting a liar.

1:20:54.646 --> 1:20:57.899
Lie to me, and you lose...

1:20:59.567 --> 1:21:01.986
the election and your freedom.

1:21:04.155 --> 1:21:06.408
But lucky for you,

1:21:06.449 --> 1:21:10.578
the truth may still set you
free
because believe it or not,

1:21:10.620 --> 1:21:14.582
I'm still grappling
with a truly punishing question.

1:21:16.334 --> 1:21:17.335
Is it worth it?

1:21:17.377 --> 1:21:21.297
(***)

1:21:27.345 --> 1:21:28.263
I don't have a party war chest.

1:21:28.304 --> 1:21:29.097
Okay?

1:21:31.224 --> 1:21:32.267
This thing
was just a temporary fix

1:21:32.308 --> 1:21:34.060
to get me to the starting line.

1:21:34.102 --> 1:21:35.395
We were gonna give it all back
as soon as we're in a position

1:21:35.437 --> 1:21:36.479
to do so.

1:21:39.274 --> 1:21:40.692
This is no harm, no foul.
It's victimless.

1:21:40.734 --> 1:21:41.693
Tell that to the class

1:21:41.735 --> 1:21:43.945
of invisible kids
in West Virginia.

1:21:46.197 --> 1:21:48.033
I don't know.

1:21:48.074 --> 1:21:48.950
How do we make this okay? Huh?

1:21:51.494 --> 1:21:53.538
First interview
after I'm sworn in.

1:21:53.580 --> 1:21:56.166
Exclusives for eight years
after that.

1:21:56.207 --> 1:21:57.709
If there's a leak
coming from the White House,

1:21:57.751 --> 1:21:59.544
you're the two pots catching
it.
You have my word!

1:22:02.589 --> 1:22:03.548
Eli.

1:22:04.716 --> 1:22:05.467
What about Penny?

1:22:07.093 --> 1:22:08.595
You worry
for your sister's safety

1:22:08.636 --> 1:22:10.597
every day
that she's serving overseas.

1:22:10.638 --> 1:22:12.557
And with your father
undergoing chemotherapy...

1:22:16.561 --> 1:22:19.481
I can't imagine how hard
that must be.

1:22:21.107 --> 1:22:22.359
And your sister, Penny, is it?

1:22:22.400 --> 1:22:24.486
Lieutenant Penelope James.

1:22:25.612 --> 1:22:27.155
We can work out

1:22:27.197 --> 1:22:29.574
an honorable discharge for her
the day I'm sworn in.

1:22:29.616 --> 1:22:31.117
Your sister deserves
to be with your dad

1:22:31.159 --> 1:22:32.160
during his treatments.

1:22:33.536 --> 1:22:35.413
If I wasn't so inexperienced,

1:22:36.706 --> 1:22:38.500
I would think you were using
a commissioned officer

1:22:38.541 --> 1:22:40.377
as collateral in a bribe.

1:22:45.131 --> 1:22:47.676
I would more call it
an agreement amongst friends.

1:22:49.511 --> 1:22:50.512
Look, I feel for you, Eli.

1:22:52.681 --> 1:22:53.807
[sighs softly]

1:22:53.848 --> 1:22:56.017
Cancer took my mom.

1:22:56.059 --> 1:22:58.269
And the emotional toll is hard.

1:22:59.354 --> 1:23:00.271
But the treatments add up.

1:23:01.731 --> 1:23:03.358
And until we can get in there
and reform

1:23:03.400 --> 1:23:06.236
the healthcare system,
I don't want your parents

1:23:06.277 --> 1:23:08.029
to be crushed under the weight
of medical bills.

1:23:09.614 --> 1:23:11.324
And we can make sure
that doesn't happen.

1:23:12.534 --> 1:23:14.369
We are on the same team here.

1:23:15.745 --> 1:23:17.706
And if you wanna make real,
lasting change,

1:23:17.747 --> 1:23:20.667
well, you just gotta play
the game,

1:23:20.709 --> 1:23:21.751
and that's the reality of it.

1:23:25.130 --> 1:23:26.798
You were supposed to change
the game.

1:23:26.840 --> 1:23:35.765
(***)

1:23:44.858 --> 1:23:53.783
(***)

1:23:55.201 --> 1:23:57.829
I had a hunch I'd find you here.

1:23:57.871 --> 1:23:59.497
ELI:
I'm getting it all down.

1:23:59.539 --> 1:24:01.541
Everything that crooked,
fucking conman's done.

1:24:01.583 --> 1:24:03.793
We don't have enough to publish.

1:24:03.835 --> 1:24:05.503
[sighs]

1:24:05.545 --> 1:24:08.131
-But he just admitted--
-Unless we find hard evidence

1:24:08.173 --> 1:24:12.177
that Sterling himself knew,
we're just a couple of trees

1:24:12.218 --> 1:24:13.678
falling in the woods.

1:24:13.720 --> 1:24:14.679
So, what do we do now?

1:24:16.097 --> 1:24:17.182
NICK:
Tear it all up.

1:24:17.223 --> 1:24:19.142
Everything we know.

1:24:19.184 --> 1:24:21.436
I'll track Sterling to his
rally
in Atlanta,

1:24:21.478 --> 1:24:25.440
and see if we can crack
the safe.

1:24:25.482 --> 1:24:34.449
(***)

1:24:43.500 --> 1:24:52.467
(***)

1:25:01.267 --> 1:25:03.645
ELI:
Mom! Dad! Where are you?

1:25:05.271 --> 1:25:06.147
I'm calling the police.

1:25:07.190 --> 1:25:07.482
They-- they trashed
my apartment!

1:25:09.818 --> 1:25:12.195
[pants]

1:25:12.237 --> 1:25:14.197
-What are you doing here?
-Thank God you're okay.

1:25:14.239 --> 1:25:16.741
-I looked everywhere.
-No. Get out, Lucas.

1:25:16.783 --> 1:25:19.285
-HAL: Eli, calm down,
sweetheart--
-ELI: Daddy.

1:25:19.327 --> 1:25:21.371
-HAL: Lucas told us.
-No. Okay?

1:25:21.413 --> 1:25:22.831
Don't believe a word
that he has to say. Okay?

1:25:24.457 --> 1:25:24.499
NATE (ON RECORDING):
This thing was just
a temporary fix

1:25:25.417 --> 1:25:25.458
to get me to the starting line.

1:25:26.334 --> 1:25:26.376
We're gonna give it all back

1:25:27.627 --> 1:25:27.669
as soon as we're in a position
to do so.

1:25:29.754 --> 1:25:31.506
This is no harm, no foul.
It's victimless!

1:25:32.966 --> 1:25:33.008
ELI (ON RECORDING):
Tell that to the class
of invisible...

1:25:33.425 --> 1:25:33.883
[gasps]

1:25:36.386 --> 1:25:37.429
Oh, my God.

1:25:39.681 --> 1:25:40.390
Did Nick know?

1:25:40.432 --> 1:25:42.183
LUCAS:
No.

1:25:42.225 --> 1:25:43.393
He still doesn't.

1:25:44.811 --> 1:25:46.771
I had to commit, or his face
would have given me away.

1:25:48.356 --> 1:25:50.400
And honestly,
I didn't decide to do it

1:25:50.442 --> 1:25:52.193
until I was standing
outside of the office.

1:25:57.866 --> 1:25:58.992
[sighs]

1:25:59.034 --> 1:26:01.411
You know,
this doesn't fix everything.

1:26:01.453 --> 1:26:02.662
LUCAS:
I know.

1:26:02.704 --> 1:26:04.205
I needed you to be wrong.

1:26:06.916 --> 1:26:07.876
I love you.

1:26:10.670 --> 1:26:11.588
It's all I got.

1:26:13.298 --> 1:26:14.257
[sighs]

1:26:16.009 --> 1:26:17.761
I need to tell Nick.

1:26:17.802 --> 1:26:20.472
He's on his way
to Sterling's rally right now.

1:26:20.513 --> 1:26:21.598
I'm flying with the campaign.

1:26:21.639 --> 1:26:23.266
I'll track him down
and tell him.

1:26:23.308 --> 1:26:24.851
-You go work on your story.
-I'll just call him.

1:26:24.893 --> 1:26:26.227
LUCAS:
That might be difficult.

1:26:26.269 --> 1:26:27.312
The last time I saw
Nick's phone,

1:26:28.188 --> 1:26:29.647
it was floating
in Sterling's coffee.

1:26:29.689 --> 1:26:30.648
[sighs]

1:26:31.900 --> 1:26:33.234
Right.

1:26:35.570 --> 1:26:36.780
CORRESPONDENT 14 (ON TV):
Nate Sterling

1:26:38.198 --> 1:26:39.282
will be in Atlanta tonight
while Senator Turnbull

1:26:39.324 --> 1:26:41.701
travels to Florida.

1:26:41.743 --> 1:26:43.995
CORRESPONDENT 15 (ON TV):
And Nate Sterling is trending on
social media as excitement...

1:26:44.037 --> 1:26:45.246
CORRESPONDENT 16 (ON TV):
Senator Turnbull leads

1:26:46.247 --> 1:26:47.540
all candidates
in total campaign spend,

1:26:49.042 --> 1:26:50.335
having raised more cash
than both Sterling and Archer

1:26:50.377 --> 1:26:51.836
for the third month in a row.

1:26:53.963 --> 1:26:54.881
ELI:
Lucas.

1:26:55.674 --> 1:26:55.757
LUCAS (OVER CELLPHONE):
Hey.

1:26:56.341 --> 1:26:56.758
Did you find him?

1:26:57.884 --> 1:26:59.052
-[indistinct chatter]
-Uh, no. Not yet.

1:26:59.094 --> 1:27:00.970
ELI (OVER CELLPHONE):
Where are you?

1:27:01.012 --> 1:27:02.972
I'm by ATB.

1:27:03.014 --> 1:27:05.016
CORRESPONDENT 17:
...A declaration
of Independence.

1:27:07.894 --> 1:27:10.605
And some are calling Sterling
the most influential...

1:27:10.647 --> 1:27:11.898
ELI (OVER CELLPHONE):
Nothing?

1:27:11.940 --> 1:27:14.359
It's like a zoo with no cages.

1:27:14.401 --> 1:27:17.487
CORRESPONDENT 18:
Here we are at Nate Sterling's
biggest rally yet.

1:27:17.529 --> 1:27:18.488
He's about to do a hit

1:27:19.280 --> 1:27:19.948
on Politics Nightly
with Jane Bower.

1:27:21.032 --> 1:27:21.282
CORRESPONDENT 19:
...Tramping its way

1:27:22.492 --> 1:27:22.909
through America's
two-party landscape.

1:27:23.576 --> 1:27:25.453
[indistinct speech]

1:27:25.495 --> 1:27:28.331
...by two points
with just one week to go.

1:27:28.373 --> 1:27:30.458
[indistinct speech]

1:27:36.339 --> 1:27:37.298
I got him.

1:27:39.843 --> 1:27:41.344
CORRESPONDENT 1:
...Just over a year ago.

1:27:41.386 --> 1:27:42.971
[indistinct shouting]

1:27:45.515 --> 1:27:47.600
LUCAS:
I-- I-- I--
I need to talk to him.

1:27:47.642 --> 1:27:49.352
-I need to talk to Mr. Booker.
