1:27:49.394 --> 1:27:50.729
JANE (ON TV):
Nate Sterling is set to take

1:27:52.230 --> 1:27:52.605
the stage any minute now
to make his closing arguments.

1:27:53.606 --> 1:27:54.899
Shit. Call back when you get
him.

1:27:56.609 --> 1:27:56.651
JANE (ON TV):
... by Nicholas Booker,
esteemed columnist

1:27:58.278 --> 1:28:00.447
for the Washington Chronicle
and lion of the fourth state.

1:28:00.488 --> 1:28:01.906
The election is a dead heat.

1:28:01.948 --> 1:28:03.199
JANE:
If it's anything

1:28:03.241 --> 1:28:04.993
like the last two elections,
it could come down

1:28:05.035 --> 1:28:07.370
to a few thousand votes
in a handful of swing states,

1:28:07.412 --> 1:28:11.875
or if it's a repeat of 2000,
a few hundred votes.

1:28:11.916 --> 1:28:14.669
Your column is read
by a few million.

1:28:14.711 --> 1:28:16.087
Your readers
really listen to you.

1:28:16.129 --> 1:28:17.380
They trust you.

1:28:17.422 --> 1:28:18.840
I call it like I see it.

1:28:18.882 --> 1:28:19.883
What do you see here?

1:28:23.678 --> 1:28:25.930
[crowd cheering]

1:28:25.972 --> 1:28:34.898
(***)

1:28:43.990 --> 1:28:51.915
(***)

1:28:52.957 --> 1:28:56.169
[chuckles]

1:28:56.211 --> 1:29:00.006
Well, I have good news
and bad news.

1:29:00.048 --> 1:29:01.591
Which do you want first?

1:29:01.633 --> 1:29:02.884
SUPPORTER (ON TV):
The bad!

1:29:02.926 --> 1:29:03.968
NATE (ON TV)
Right!

1:29:04.010 --> 1:29:06.888
Okay, here it is.

1:29:08.598 --> 1:29:11.851
My little girl
turned 21 yesterday.

1:29:13.561 --> 1:29:15.063
And the first thing Alison did
was make sure

1:29:15.105 --> 1:29:16.940
her voter registration
was current.

1:29:16.981 --> 1:29:18.733
[crowd cheering]

1:29:21.778 --> 1:29:22.737
Hello.

1:29:23.863 --> 1:29:25.407
No. No, no, no, no.
Slow down.

1:29:31.496 --> 1:29:32.455
Okay.

1:29:33.748 --> 1:29:34.749
Okay.

1:29:34.791 --> 1:29:43.758
(***)

1:29:52.809 --> 1:29:56.771
(***)

1:30:00.900 --> 1:30:02.235
...And the other just sits
on its hands

1:30:02.277 --> 1:30:03.194
and whines about it.

1:30:08.450 --> 1:30:09.784
'Cause Alison deserves better.

1:30:09.826 --> 1:30:12.787
Our young people deserve better.

1:30:12.829 --> 1:30:14.831
They deserve to look
forward to the future

1:30:14.873 --> 1:30:19.085
the way we used to with hope,
with pride, with excitement.

1:30:19.127 --> 1:30:20.086
Holy shit.

1:30:20.128 --> 1:30:21.087
GORDON:
"Holy shit" what?

1:30:21.129 --> 1:30:25.091
(***)

1:30:26.134 --> 1:30:27.135
Holy...

1:30:28.178 --> 1:30:28.928
This is unreal.

1:30:42.650 --> 1:30:43.818
LUCAS:
Oh. Hey, Lynn. I got it.

1:30:46.279 --> 1:30:47.655
[sighs]

1:30:52.202 --> 1:30:55.080
So sorry for your loss,
Mrs. James.

1:30:55.121 --> 1:30:56.706
LYNN:
Thank you.

1:30:56.748 --> 1:30:59.626
And thank you for being so good
to my daughter.

1:30:59.668 --> 1:31:02.712
You and your husband have
raised
a fine young woman.

1:31:10.261 --> 1:31:12.263
Let's...

1:31:12.305 --> 1:31:14.015
How fast can you finish
the story?

1:31:17.936 --> 1:31:19.521
I'm about to bury my dad.

1:31:23.191 --> 1:31:24.609
Maybe you should just take over.

1:31:25.985 --> 1:31:28.113
It's your story.

1:31:28.154 --> 1:31:30.865
You found it. You pushed it.
You're writing it.

1:31:33.535 --> 1:31:36.037
And if we're doing it,
we gotta be quick.

1:31:36.079 --> 1:31:37.831
We've got 24 hours, tops.

1:31:38.873 --> 1:31:40.792
And it's gotta be airtight.

1:31:41.876 --> 1:31:43.044
I'll take care of the rest.

1:31:45.296 --> 1:31:46.214
And...

1:31:49.551 --> 1:31:50.719
I'm sorry about your father.

1:32:07.777 --> 1:32:09.279
Hello, Eli.

1:32:09.320 --> 1:32:10.572
ELI (OVER PHONE):
Nick and I have a story

1:32:11.740 --> 1:32:12.741
ready for publication
that just might decide

1:32:13.908 --> 1:32:15.160
the next president
of the United States.

1:32:15.201 --> 1:32:17.037
Is that so?

1:32:17.078 --> 1:32:18.705
Should I be worried?

1:32:18.747 --> 1:32:21.207
Why do you wanna be president,
Senator Turnbull?

1:32:22.334 --> 1:32:23.835
TURNBULL (OVER PHONE):
Look, Eli.

1:32:23.877 --> 1:32:27.380
I assume we don't agree
on most policy.

1:32:27.422 --> 1:32:30.633
But one thing we do both value
is the truth.

1:32:30.675 --> 1:32:32.719
So, I'm gonna give you mine.

1:32:32.761 --> 1:32:36.056
Right now, I am running
as the leader of my party,

1:32:36.097 --> 1:32:37.891
but should
I be fortunate enough

1:32:37.932 --> 1:32:39.976
to take that oath
on January 20,

1:32:41.019 --> 1:32:44.314
I will be governing
as the leader of my country.

1:32:46.149 --> 1:32:48.026
Our democracy is fragile.

1:32:49.611 --> 1:32:52.906
You protect it from the outside
by doing what you do.

1:32:52.947 --> 1:32:55.158
And if I get the chance,
I'm going to protect it

1:32:55.200 --> 1:32:58.787
from the inside
with everything I've got.

1:33:00.288 --> 1:33:01.289
ELI:
And off the record?

1:33:04.167 --> 1:33:05.168
Take care, Eli.

1:33:12.300 --> 1:33:21.267
(***)

1:33:30.318 --> 1:33:34.280
(***)

1:33:40.203 --> 1:33:41.955
[chuckles softly]

1:33:41.996 --> 1:33:50.964
(***)

1:34:00.015 --> 1:34:08.982
(***)

1:34:18.033 --> 1:34:27.000
(***)

1:34:28.209 --> 1:34:29.502
I don't understand.

1:34:29.544 --> 1:34:32.088
What's-- what's so special
about this one?

1:34:36.134 --> 1:34:37.260
LYNN:
The day you were born.

1:34:40.972 --> 1:34:41.931
[sighs]

1:34:45.143 --> 1:34:46.478
I never got to say goodbye.

1:34:48.063 --> 1:34:50.482
We thought it was another
false alarm from the chemo.

1:34:52.984 --> 1:34:55.195
He knew that you were
at the Chronicle, writing.

1:34:55.236 --> 1:34:56.780
[sighs]

1:34:56.821 --> 1:34:58.031
LYNN:
He insisted

1:34:58.073 --> 1:34:59.908
that that was where you needed
to be.

1:35:02.952 --> 1:35:04.746
He loved you.

1:35:07.332 --> 1:35:08.917
He's so proud.

1:35:12.337 --> 1:35:13.338
[kisses]

1:35:13.380 --> 1:35:21.930
(***)

1:35:22.972 --> 1:35:25.100
[chuckles softly]

1:35:25.141 --> 1:35:26.101
Daddy.

1:35:26.142 --> 1:35:35.110
(***)

1:35:38.363 --> 1:35:39.322
Okay.

1:35:44.119 --> 1:35:45.078
[sniffles]

1:35:45.120 --> 1:35:54.045
(***)

1:36:03.138 --> 1:36:12.063
(***)

1:36:15.859 --> 1:36:16.901
[sniffles]

1:36:16.943 --> 1:36:18.945
[phone rings]

1:36:24.367 --> 1:36:25.452
KEVIN (OVER CELLPHONE):
Where are you?

1:36:25.493 --> 1:36:27.370
-Kevin?
-Hey, where are you?

1:36:27.412 --> 1:36:28.538
ELI (OVER CELLPHONE):
I'm at my parents' house.

1:36:28.580 --> 1:36:29.956
All right.

1:36:29.998 --> 1:36:30.498
Meet me at the diner
on 4th and Delaware

1:36:31.249 --> 1:36:32.417
in 20 minutes. All right?

1:36:34.210 --> 1:36:34.252
-I'm not doing that.
-KEVIN (OVER CELLPHONE): It's an
emergency.

1:36:34.919 --> 1:36:34.961
What is this about?

1:36:35.587 --> 1:36:36.296
Look, I was fired.

1:36:36.338 --> 1:36:37.255
Why?

1:36:37.297 --> 1:36:38.882
Because I-- I know the names,

1:36:38.923 --> 1:36:41.259
Tom Mayfield, Dean Clifton,
and Spencer Erickson.

1:36:46.181 --> 1:36:47.974
[indistinct chatter]

1:36:51.478 --> 1:36:53.480
How the fuck do you know
those names?

1:36:53.521 --> 1:36:55.315
The-- the um-- the other night

1:36:55.357 --> 1:36:58.026
when you got that call
and you left in a hurry,

1:36:59.611 --> 1:37:03.573
well, you didn't log out.
And Gordon assumed it was mine.

1:37:05.325 --> 1:37:08.495
Look, I didn't say anything,
'cause I was in shock

1:37:08.536 --> 1:37:10.246
and Gordon flipped for it.

1:37:10.288 --> 1:37:11.289
I thought I'd be waking up
to a headline

1:37:12.415 --> 1:37:13.375
that would change
the course of history.

1:37:14.584 --> 1:37:15.627
So, why did I instead wake up
to an email

1:37:17.212 --> 1:37:18.129
informing me that the Chronicle
was terminating my contract?

1:37:18.838 --> 1:37:19.339
I mean, I rushed to the office,

1:37:20.715 --> 1:37:21.091
and security wouldn't even
let me in the building.

1:37:22.258 --> 1:37:23.927
Apparently, Gordon had HR
clean out my desk

1:37:23.968 --> 1:37:25.178
and wipe my desktop.

1:37:25.220 --> 1:37:27.097
Gordon killed the story
to save his own ass.

1:37:28.473 --> 1:37:30.517
-Why-- why would he--
- ELI: Jack Hampton.

1:37:30.558 --> 1:37:32.519
He's a huge Sterling supporter.

1:37:32.560 --> 1:37:33.520
Gordon prints the story,

1:37:34.604 --> 1:37:35.063
Hampton orders
his head on a platter.

1:37:36.189 --> 1:37:37.357
Gordon kills the story,
Sterling wins.

1:37:37.399 --> 1:37:38.525
Guess which paper
has a direct line

1:37:38.566 --> 1:37:39.526
to the Oval Office.

1:37:42.570 --> 1:37:45.281
So, Gordon is playing politics

1:37:45.323 --> 1:37:47.992
dirtier
than the goddamn politicians?

1:37:50.412 --> 1:37:51.371
[scoffs]

1:37:54.624 --> 1:37:57.419
Please nail that motherfucker.

1:37:58.503 --> 1:37:59.587
I can't believe

1:37:59.629 --> 1:38:01.006
you let Gordon think
it was your story.

1:38:03.216 --> 1:38:06.594
Look. I never said that it was.

1:38:06.636 --> 1:38:08.972
And as it turns out,
I did you a favor.

1:38:10.557 --> 1:38:12.559
So, you're welcome. Hmm?

1:38:19.607 --> 1:38:21.109
No, Eli. I got it. Please.

1:38:22.235 --> 1:38:23.236
You're unemployed.

1:38:23.278 --> 1:38:25.280
It wouldn't be right. Prick.

1:38:30.952 --> 1:38:32.120
Have you shown Gordon the story?

1:38:33.121 --> 1:38:33.204
NICK (OVER CELLPHONE):
I'm waiting for you.

1:38:34.539 --> 1:38:34.581
You should get to see
the look on his face.

1:38:35.874 --> 1:38:36.708
-Where the fuck are you?
-I'm on my way.

1:38:37.792 --> 1:38:39.085
Whatever you do,
don't talk to Gordon.

1:38:43.089 --> 1:38:45.467
And I thought I'd seen it all.

1:38:50.388 --> 1:38:51.389
We're doing this?

1:38:51.431 --> 1:38:53.016
[chuckles]

1:38:54.309 --> 1:38:56.227
ELI:
What?

1:38:56.269 --> 1:38:58.563
The weight of the world
lies in the palm of my hand.

1:38:58.605 --> 1:39:00.482
I guess I thought
it'd be a bit heavier.

1:39:01.566 --> 1:39:03.318
[chuckles softly]

1:39:03.360 --> 1:39:07.072
You know what this means
if we go through with this.

1:39:11.534 --> 1:39:13.161
And you're willing?

1:39:13.203 --> 1:39:16.206
I guess that's why they call it
the moment of truth.

1:39:18.750 --> 1:39:20.001
It's your story.

1:39:23.296 --> 1:39:24.673
What?

1:39:24.714 --> 1:39:27.592
No. I-- I stumbled upon it,
yeah, but you guided me.

1:39:30.762 --> 1:39:32.806
If you hadn't have gotten me
that interview

1:39:32.847 --> 1:39:35.600
-at Meyers & Goldstein--
-You would have gotten it
in some other way.

1:39:35.642 --> 1:39:36.685
I doubted you.

1:39:38.395 --> 1:39:40.397
You fought through the doubt.

1:39:40.438 --> 1:39:41.523
You took me for the ride.

1:39:43.149 --> 1:39:45.610
I didn't provide anything
that you didn't already--

1:39:45.652 --> 1:39:47.362
You can now.

1:39:47.404 --> 1:39:48.196
What?

1:39:48.238 --> 1:39:49.239
Credibility.

1:39:50.532 --> 1:39:52.742
Sterling was right.
Nobody knows my name.

1:39:52.784 --> 1:39:56.329
And those that do
aren't so fond of it.

1:39:56.371 --> 1:39:58.289
If I were to publish this
on my own,

1:39:58.331 --> 1:40:01.543
it wouldn't get any traction.
Or worse, it'll get dismissed.

1:40:03.253 --> 1:40:06.715
But coming from Nicholas
Booker,
it'll be on every front page

1:40:06.756 --> 1:40:08.591
and television network
in minutes.

1:40:09.843 --> 1:40:11.386
We need to do this together.

1:40:12.804 --> 1:40:15.390
And after we break the story,
we can set up our own shop.

1:40:16.850 --> 1:40:19.227
No editor or parent corporation

1:40:19.269 --> 1:40:21.521
to tell us what
we can and can't print.

1:40:21.563 --> 1:40:25.525
A publication that answers
to nothing but the facts,

1:40:25.567 --> 1:40:26.568
wherever they lead.

1:40:28.611 --> 1:40:29.654
What would we call it?

1:40:32.198 --> 1:40:33.116
The Independent.

1:40:36.661 --> 1:40:37.787
The Independent.

1:40:37.829 --> 1:40:46.755
(***)

1:40:54.763 --> 1:40:56.723
[breathes deeply]

1:40:56.765 --> 1:41:06.733
(***)

1:41:13.198 --> 1:41:14.407
You do the honors.

1:41:14.449 --> 1:41:23.416
(***)

1:41:33.843 --> 1:41:34.844
[chuckles]

1:41:36.638 --> 1:41:37.597
Thank you.

1:41:37.639 --> 1:41:46.606
(***)

1:41:49.651 --> 1:41:50.735
Now, what?

1:41:51.986 --> 1:41:53.321
What do you say
we get the hell out of here?

1:41:55.323 --> 1:41:56.783
And go where?

1:41:56.825 --> 1:41:58.785
Watch the fireworks
from the hill.

1:41:58.827 --> 1:42:02.789
(***)

